{"title_page": "Brian Fallon discography", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist          = [[Brian Fallon]]\n| Image           = Brian_Fallon,_%27Songs_from_the_Hymnal%27_tour,_The_Junction,_Cambridge,_UK,_22_February_2019.jpg\n| Caption         = Brian Fallon performing solo at Cambridge, UK, 2019.\n| Studio          = 3\n| EP              = 1\n| Compilation     = \n| Live            =\n| Video           =    \n| Music videos    = 8\n| Singles         = 8\n}}\nThe discography of [[Brian Fallon]], an American singer-songwriter and musician. His debut studio album, ''[[Painkillers (Brian Fallon album)|Painkillers]]'', was released in March 2016. The album peaked at number thirty on the [[Billboard 200]]. The album includes the single \"A Wonderful Life\". His second studio album, ''[[Sleepwalkers (Brian Fallon album)|Sleepwalkers]]'', was released in February 2018. The album peaked at number forty-two on the [[Billboard 200]]. The album includes the singles \"Forget Me Not\", \"If Your Prayers Don't Get to Heaven\", \"See You on the Other Side\" and \"My Name Is the Night (Color Me Black)\". His third studio album, ''[[Local Honey]]'', was released in March 2020. The album includes the singles \"You Have Stolen My Heart\", \"21 Days\" and \"When You're Ready\".\n\n==Studio albums==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:22em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"9\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Brian-Fallon/chart-history/TLP|title=Brian Fallon (Billboard 200)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Brian+