{"title_page": "Puffle", "text_new": "Puffles are [[Fiction|Fictional]] Creatures from the Children's Video Game [[Club Penguin]. Puffles were first released in November of 2005 and were first adoptable in March of 2006. According to the staff to the [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle club penguin fandom] their favorite foods are Puffle-O's and O-Berries. In the game there were 4 Puffle Centric games, [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle_Launch Puffle Launch], [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Pufflescape Pufflescape], [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle_Roundup Puffle Roundup], [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Thin_Ice Thin Ice] and [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle_Rescue Puffle Rescue]. In the original Club Penguin you adopt Golden Puffles, Blue Puffles, Red Puffles, Yellow Puffles, Green Puffles, Orange Puffles, Pink Puffles, Purple Puffles, Black Puffles, White Puffles, and Rainbow Puffles. You could also adopt special \"Puffle Creatures\" such as the Dog and Cat Puffles, Alien Puffles, Blue Crystal Puffles, Snowman Puffles (made for the frozen party), and Dinosaur Puffles. In Club Penguin Rewritten you can adopt an additional Grey Puffle. Similarly in Club Penguin Online you can adopt Silver and Teal Puffles. [[File:Home-Made Blue Puffle.JPG|thumb|This is a homemade drawing of a Blue Puffle, The Most Popular Type of Puffle]]. There was also a Puffle Launch App which existed from September 14 2011 to July 2nd 2013.\n", "text_old": "Puffles are [[Fiction|Fictional]] Creatures from the Children's Video Game [[Club Penguin]. Puffles were first released in November of 2005 and were first adoptable in March of 2006. According to the staff to the [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle club penguin fandom] their favorite foods are Puffle-O's and O-Berries. In the game there were 4 Puffle centric games, [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle_Launch Puffle Launch], [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Pufflescape Pufflescape], [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle_Roundup Puffle Roundup], [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Thin_Ice Thin Ice] and [https://clubpenguin.fandom.com/wiki/Puffle_Rescue Puffle Rescue]. In the original Club Penguin you adopt Golden Puffles, Blue Puffles, Red Puffles, Yellow Puffles, Green Puffles, Orange Puffles, Pink Puffles, Purple Puffles, Black Puffles, White Puffles, and Rainbow Puffles. You could also adopt special \"Puffle Creatures\" such as the Dog and Cat Puffles, Alien Puffles, Blue Crystal Puffles, Snowman Puffles (made for the frozen party), and Dinosaur Puffles. In Club Penguin Rewritten you can adopt an additional Grey Puffle. Similarly in Club Penguin Online you can adopt Silver and Teal Puffles. [[File:Home-Made Blue Puffle.JPG|thumb|This is a homemade drawing of a Blue Puffle, The Most Popular Type of Puffle]]\n", "name_user": "Niobaker123890", "label": "safe", "comment": "just added one sentence", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puffle"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil", "text_new": "{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{dablinks|date=March 2020}}\n{{Overlinked|date=April 2020}}}}\n\n{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Brazil}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil\n| map1            = COVID-19_Outbreak_Cases_in_Brazil.svg\n| legend1         = Map of states with confirmed coronavirus cases (as of 1 April)\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Brazil]]\n| first_case      = S\u00e3o Paulo\n| arrival_date    = 26 February 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=2|day1=25|year1=2020}})\n| origin          = [[Lombardy]], Italy<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga poss\u00edvel paciente com coronav\u00edrus em SP; caso foi para contraprova|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = 120\n| deaths          = 241<ref name=Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade/>\n| confirmed_cases = 6,836<ref name=\"Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade\">{{cite web |url=https://saude.gov.br/ |title=Casos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil em 1 de abril |language=Portuguese |work=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324202227/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/24/brasil-tem-46-mortes-e-casos-2201confirmados-de-covid-19-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = 63,516<ref name=Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade/>\n| total_ili       = |website|P.s: Several states in the country confirmed cases after the closure of the Ministry of Health. Brazil is a Federative Republic, divided into 27 federative units, of which confirm results before the federal government.\n| website         = {{URL|https://coronavirus.saude.gov.br/}}\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Brazil]] on 25 February 2020, after a 61-year-old man from [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] who had returned from [[Lombardy]], Italy tested positive for the virus. Since then, as of 22 March 2020, 6,836 cases were confirmed in the country, causing 241 deaths.<ref name=\"Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade\"/> Local transmission has been reported in at least seven states{{cn|date=April 2020}}, and the pandemic has triggered a variety of responses from federal, state and local governments, while also impacting politics, education and the economy.\n\n== Current number of cases by states ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable col3der\"\n|-\n! State !! Confirmed Cases !! Confirmed Deaths\n|-\n| {{flag|S\u00e3o Paulo}} || 2981 || 164\n|-\n| {{flag|Minas Gerais}}|| 314 || 3\n|-\n| {{flag|Rio de Janeiro}} || 832 || 28\n|-\n| {{flag|Bahia}}|| 246 || 2\n|-\n| {{flag|Rio Grande do Sul}}|| 306 || 4\n|-\n| {{flag|Paran\u00e1}}|| 224 || 3\n|-\n| {{flag|Pernambuco}} || 95 || 8\n|-\n| {{flag|Cear\u00e1}} || 444 || 8\n|-\n| {{flag|Par\u00e1}} || 40 || 1\n|-\n| {{flag|Goi\u00e1s}} || 71 || 1\n|-\n| {{flag|Maranh\u00e3o}}|| 54 || 1\n|-\n| {{flag|Santa Catarina}} || 235 || 2\n|-\n| {{flag|Para\u00edba}} || 20 || 1\n|-\n| {{flag|Amazonas}} || 200 || 3\n|-\n| {{flag|Esp\u00edrito Santo}}|| 96 || 0\n|-\n| {{flag|Rio Grande do Norte}}|| 92 || 2\n|-\n| {{flag|Alagoas}}|| 18 || 1\n|-\n| {{flag|Mato Grosso}} || 27 || 0\n|-\n| {{flag|Piau\u00ed}} || 18 || 4\n|-\n| {{flag|Distrito Federal}}|| 355 || 3\n|-\n| {{flag|Mato Grosso do Sul}}|| 51 || 1\n|-\n| {{flag|Sergipe}}|| 20 || 0\n|-\n| {{flag|Rond\u00f4nia}}|| 9 || 1\n|-\n| {{flag|Tocantins}}|| 12 || 0\n|-\n| {{flag|Acre}} || 43 || 0\n|-\n| {{flag|Amap\u00e1}} || 11 || 0\n|-\n| {{flag|Roraima}}|| 22 || 0\n|-\n!{{flag|Brazil}}|| 6,836 || 241\n|}\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Brazil medical cases chart}}\nThese are the deaths and new confirmed cases of the new Coronavirus in Brazil.\n\n===January and February===\nOn 28 January 2020, the [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Ministry of Health]] (''Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade'') raised the emergency alert to level 2 of 3, considering an \"imminent threat\" for Brazil, as a suspected case was being investigated in [[Belo Horizonte]], Minas Gerais.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-caso-suspeito-de-coronavirus-em-mg.ghtml |title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga caso suspeito de coronav\u00edrus em MG |last= Cruz |first= Carolina |date= 28 January 2020 |accessdate=28 January 2020 | work = G1 |language= pt-br |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200128142750/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-caso-suspeito-de-coronavirus-em-mg.ghtml |archive-date=28 January 2020 |url-status= live}}</ref> The following day, the Ministry announced it was investigating two other suspected cases, in [[Porto Alegre]] and [[Curitiba]]. No further information was given about the patients in Porto Alegre and Curitiba. However, it was informed that the Belo Horizonte patient was a student that had recently visited [[Wuhan]], China, point of origin of the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-3-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil/|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade confirma 3 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|date=28 January 2020|publisher=Exame Abril|accessdate=29 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129042253/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-3-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil/|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 February, the Minister of Health [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]] said that the Brazilian government would declare a [[Public Health Emergency of International Concern]], even without confirmed cases in the country. He also said the government would assist on the return of Brazilians from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/03/nao-gosto-de-trabalhar-com-prazo-diz-ministro-da-saude-sobre-repatriacao-de-brasileiros-de-wuhan.ghtml|title=Pa\u00eds adotar\u00e1 emerg\u00eancia para retirar cidad\u00e3os de \u00e1rea de surto de coronav\u00edrus, diz ministro|date=3 February 2020|publisher=G1|accessdate=3 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203161354/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/03/nao-gosto-de-trabalhar-com-prazo-diz-ministro-da-saude-sobre-repatriacao-de-brasileiros-de-wuhan.ghtml|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, the Ministry confirmed that around 30 Brazilians were in Wuhan, and that they would return to the country on 8 February. It was also announced that they would be [[quarantine]]d for 18 days in [[An\u00e1polis]], Goi\u00e1s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/04/coronavirus-brasileiros-na-china-devem-chegar-ao-pais-no-sabado-e-cumprir-quarentena-em-anapolis.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: brasileiros na China devem chegar ao pa\u00eds no s\u00e1bado e cumprir quarentena em An\u00e1polis|date=4 February 2020|publisher=G1|accessdate=4 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205010554/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/04/coronavirus-brasileiros-na-china-devem-chegar-ao-pais-no-sabado-e-cumprir-quarentena-em-anapolis.ghtml|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 February, the Brazilian government sent two planes to evacuate 34 Brazilians from [[Wuhan]]. They and the flight crew were quarantined at a [[Brazilian Air Force]] base in An\u00e1polis,<ref>{{cite news|first1=Pedro Henrique|last1=Gomes|date=5 February 2020 |url= https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/05/coronavirus-avioes-da-fab-decolam-em-viagem-para-buscar-brasileiros-na-china.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: avi\u00f5es da FAB decolam de Bras\u00edlia para buscar brasileiros na China |work=G1|accessdate=5 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200205214039/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/05/coronavirus-avioes-da-fab-decolam-em-viagem-para-buscar-brasileiros-na-china.ghtml |archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and discharged, along with the doctors and health professionals who had contact with them, on 23 February, four days earlier than predicted, as routine tests repeatedly showed negative results for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|date=23 February 2020|url= https://www.bbc.com/portuguese/geral-51605693 |title=Coronav\u00edrus: Brasileiros s\u00e3o liberados da quarentena e deixam An\u00e1polis|work= BBC News Brasil |accessdate= 23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 February, the Ministry announced nine suspected cases in the country in five different states. However, these were later dismissed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/02/06/brasil-tem-8-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Brasil descarta mais 3 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus e investiga 9, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=6 February 2020|publisher=G1|accessdate=6 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206140633/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/02/06/brasil-tem-8-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 24 February, it was informed by the Ministry that there was officially four suspected cases in the country after 54 cases were dismissed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/02/24/brasil-tem-4-casos-suspeitos-de-novo-coronavirus-informa-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|work=G1|publisher=Globo.com|title=Brasil tem 4 casos suspeitos de novo coronav\u00edrus; outros 54 foram descartados|accessdate=25 February 2020|date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225022000/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/02/24/brasil-tem-4-casos-suspeitos-de-novo-coronavirus-informa-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February, the Health Department of S\u00e3o Paulo reported the first case of COVID-19 in Brazil \u2013 and in South America. It was a 61-year-old man from [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], S\u00e3o Paulo who travelled through [[Lombardy]], Italy between 9 and 21 February. He tested positive for [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]] at [[Albert Einstein Israelite Hospital]], which was also confirmed by the Adolfo Lutz Institute. The patient was showing mild symptoms and had been quarantined at home.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml |title= Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga poss\u00edvel paciente com coronav\u00edrus em SP; caso foi para contraprova| work =G1|date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/equilibrioesaude/2020/02/brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-do-novo-coronavirus.shtml|title= Brasil confirma primeiro caso do novo coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S. Paulo|date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, following the first confirmed case in the country, the government reported that Brazil was monitoring 20 suspected cases, 12 of them were people who came from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/02/26/ministerio-da-saude-coronavirus-brasil-primeiro-caso-contraprova.htm|title=Governo confirma 1\u00ba caso, mas diz que avaliar\u00e1 coronav\u00edrus em pa\u00eds tropical|website=UOL|date=26 February 2020}}</ref> The following day, Brazil reported 132 suspected cases in 16 states, 85 of them in the state of S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/27/brasil-tem-132-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus.ghtml|title= Brasil tem 132 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus|work= G1|date= 27 February 2020|access-date= 27 February 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200227203936/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/27/brasil-tem-132-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date= 27 February 2020|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, the Brazilian government reported 182 suspected cases in 17 states; 72 of the previous day cases were discarded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/brasil-tem-182-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 182 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|work=G1|date=28 February 2020|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228221411/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/brasil-tem-182-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> That same day, Brazilian scientists from Adolfo Lutz Institute and the [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]]'s Tropical Medicine Institute \u2014 part of the Centre for Arbovirus Discovery, Diagnostics, Genomics & Epidemiology \u2014 announced the sequencing of the COVID-19 [[genome]] of the first case reported in Brazil, in a record time of just two days.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409|title= Projecto CADDE \u2013 Primeiro genoma de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|website= R7|date= 29 February 2020|access-date= 4 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200305042115/http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409|archive-date= 5 March 2020|url-status= live}}</ref> This discovery will assist in improving the diagnosis and control measures to curb the spread of the disease.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/cientistas-do-brasil-e-de-oxford-sequenciam-genoma-do-novo-coronavirus-detectado-em-sp.ghtml|title=Cientistas do Brasil e de Oxford sequenciam genoma do novo coronav\u00edrus detectado em SP|website=G1 Bem Estar|date=28 February 2020|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228213521/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/cientistas-do-brasil-e-de-oxford-sequenciam-genoma-do-novo-coronavirus-detectado-em-sp.ghtml|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 February, a second case was confirmed in the country: the patient was a 32-year-old man who arrived from [[Milan]]. Brazil also reported 207 suspected cases in 17 states, 91 of them in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://noticias.r7.com/saude/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-e-confirmado-em-sp-29022020|title= Segundo caso de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil \u00e9 confirmado em SP|website= R7|date= 29 February 2020|access-date= 29 February 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200229203856/https://noticias.r7.com/saude/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-e-confirmado-em-sp-29022020|archive-date= 29 February 2020|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n===1\u201315 March===\nOn 3 March, Brazil raised the number of suspected cases from 433 to 488 in 23 states.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|title=Notifica\u00e7\u00e3o de casos de doen\u00e7a pelo coronav\u00edrus 2019 (COVID-19)|website=Ministerio da Saude|date=4 March 2020|access-date=4 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227111830/http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> That same day, the genome of COVID-19 samples from the second Brazilian case were released on the [[GISAID]] database. The analysis shows two independent introductions of the virus in Brazil from [[Northern Italy]] and have direct implications in understanding the outbreak in Italy.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409 |title= Projeto Cadde \u2013 Segundo genoma de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil |website= Virological |date= 29 February 2020 |access-date= 4 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200305042115/http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409 |archive-date= 5 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> The following day, two additional cases of COVID-19 were confirmed, raising the number of infected patients to 4. The number of suspected cases was raised from 488 to 531.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/04/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-terceiro-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-um-quarto-caso-aguarda-contraprova.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade confirma terceiro paciente com coronav\u00edrus no Brasil; quarto caso em SP aguarda contraprova|website=G1|date=4 March 2020}}</ref> Up until that moment, all of the confirmed cases were from the state of S\u00e3o Paulo.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n[[File:Pronunciamento oficial do Presidente Jair Bolsonaro sobre COVID-19.webm|thumb|right|upright=1.25|right|start=00:00|thumbtime=00:39|President [[Jair Bolsonaro]]'s official announcement about COVID-19, 6 March.]]\n\nOn 5 March, three new cases were confirmed, raising the total to 8. The disease had now spread to the states of [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]] and [[Esp\u00edrito Santo]], also in the [[Southeast Region, Brazil|Southeast Region]]. Later that day, a woman in the [[Federal District (Brazil)|Federal District]] was hospitalized after testing positive for COVID-19 and was waiting for the confirmation test.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/df/distrito-federal/noticia/2020/03/05/paciente-que-testou-positivo-para-coronavirus-no-df-esta-internada-em-uti.ghtml|title=Paciente que testou positivo para coronav\u00edrus no DF est\u00e1 internada em UTI|website=G1 DF|date=5 March 2020|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306151707/https://g1.globo.com/df/distrito-federal/noticia/2020/03/05/paciente-que-testou-positivo-para-coronavirus-no-df-esta-internada-em-uti.ghtml|archive-date=6 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> That was the first case reported in the [[Central-West Region, Brazil|Central-West Region]].\n\nOn 6 March, the country raised the number of confirmed cases to 13. The state of [[Bahia]] \u2014 and [[Northeast Region, Brazil|Northeast Region]] \u2014 confirmed its first case, and the number of suspected cases was raised to 768.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-tem-13-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-06032020|title=Brasil tem 13 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|website=R7|date=6 March 2020}}</ref> That same day, Brazilian scientists announced the cultivation of COVID-19 in a laboratory, with the purpose of contributing to the diagnosis and vaccines against the disease.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/pesquisadores-brasileiros-produzem-novo-coronavirus-em-laboratorio.ghtml|title=Pesquisadores brasileiros desenvolvem 'novo coronav\u00edrus' em laborat\u00f3rio; material vai ajudar no diagn\u00f3stico da doen\u00e7a|website=Bem Estar|date=6 March 2020|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323140422/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/pesquisadores-brasileiros-produzem-novo-coronavirus-em-laboratorio.ghtml|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, President [[Jair Bolsonaro]], said during an official announcement on television that \"there is no reason to panic\" and that people \"must strictly follow the experts recommendations as the best protective measure\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/ainda-que-o-problema-possa-se-agravar-nao-ha-motivo-para-panico-diz-bolsonaro-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Bolsonaro diz na TV que n\u00e3o h\u00e1 raz\u00e3o para p\u00e2nico ainda que problema se agrave|website=G1|date=6 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307124400/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/ainda-que-o-problema-possa-se-agravar-nao-ha-motivo-para-panico-diz-bolsonaro-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=7 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 March, the Ministry of Health confirmed 6 new cases, raising the number to 19. The number of suspected cases was reduced to 674.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/07/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-17-casos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade confirma quatro novos casos do novo coronav\u00edrus; agora s\u00e3o 19 no pa\u00eds|date=7 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308053450/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/07/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-17-casos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=8 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, six new cases were confirmed, raising the total number to 25. The states of [[Alagoas]] (in the Northeast) and [[Minas Gerais]] (in the Southeast) reported their first cases.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/08/brasil-tem-21-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 25 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus|date=8 March 2020|access-date=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309122600/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/08/brasil-tem-21-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=9 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, the country confirmed 5 new cases of coronavirus \u2013 all of them in the state of Rio de Janeiro \u2014, raising the total number to 30. The number of suspected cases was raised to 930.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/09/rj-confirma-mais-5-casos-e-chega-a-8-infectados-pelo-novo-coronavirus.ghtml|title=RJ confirma mais 5 casos do novo coronav\u00edrus e total de infectados chega a 8|date=9 March 2020|access-date=9 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310033132/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/09/rj-confirma-mais-5-casos-e-chega-a-8-infectados-pelo-novo-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, Brazil confirmed four new cases, raising the number to 34. The disease had spread to the [[South Region, Brazil|Southern Region]], with the state of [[Rio Grande do Sul]] confirming its first case. The number of suspected cases was reduced to 893.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/10/brasil-tem-34-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 34 casos confirmados de novo coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|date=10 March 2020|access-date=10 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310202031/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/10/brasil-tem-34-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March, the Federal District confirmed a second case of COVID-19. The patient was the husband of the woman who was hospitalized on 5 March. The examination was carried out by a court order. He had refused to be quarantined and had been in regular contact with others.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/df/distrito-federal/noticia/2020/03/10/coronavirus-apos-determinacao-da-justica-marido-de-paciente-infectada-passa-por-exames-no-df.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: GDF pede e ju\u00edza obriga marido de paciente infectada a passar por exames|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Later that day, the total number of cases in the country was raised to 69, with new cases being confirmed in the states of S\u00e3o Paulo, Rio de Janeiro, Rio Grande do Sul, and Bahia.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/equilibrioesaude/2020/03/sobe-para-37-o-numero-de-casos-do-novo-coronavirus-no-brasil.shtml|title=Sobe para 64 o n\u00famero de casos do novo coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|date=11 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312130741/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/equilibrioesaude/2020/03/sobe-para-37-o-numero-de-casos-do-novo-coronavirus-no-brasil.shtml|archive-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, Brazil confirmed 137 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/brasil-tem-76-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 137 casos confirmados de novo coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|date=n.d.|website=G1|language=pt-br|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317203317/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/brasil-tem-76-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|archive-date=17 March 2020|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> The state of [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]] (in the South) confirmed its first 6 cases, while [[Pernambuco]] (in the Northeast) confirmed its first two cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/pr/parana/noticia/2020/03/12/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-seis-casos-do-novo-coronavirus-no-parana.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade confirma seis casos do novo coronav\u00edrus no Paran\u00e1|website=G1 PR|date=12 March 2020}}</ref> F\u00e1bio Wajngarten, Press Secretary to President Bolsonaro, tested positive for COVID-19. As such, the president and his cabinet were being monitored. Wajngarten had also interacted with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and Vice President [[Mike Pence]], during Bolsonaro's visit to Miami on 7 March, raising concerns that he might have infected them.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/exame-de-fabio-wajngarten-para-coronavirus-da-positivo-24300536|title=Exame de Fabio Wajngarten para coronav\u00edrus d\u00e1 positivo|website=O Globo|date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312220550/https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/exame-de-fabio-wajngarten-para-coronavirus-da-positivo-24300536|archive-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Also on 12 March, the Ministry of Health requested the approval of an additional R$10&nbsp;billion (US$2.1&nbsp;billion) in the federal budget to reinforce its fight against the disease in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.infomoney.com.br/economia/guedes-diz-que-governo-negocia-r-10-bi-para-combate-ao-coronavirus-ha-espaco-para-medidas-emergenciais/|title=Guedes diz que governo negocia R$10 bi para combate ao coronav\u00edrus: h\u00e1 espa\u00e7o para medidas emergenciais|website=Infomoney|date=12 March 2020}}</ref> It also estimated that 2,000 intensive care units will be needed to treat patients in the coming weeks.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/sus-preve-2-mil-leitos-de-uti-para-tratar-pacientes-com-covid-19.ghtml|title=SUS prev\u00ea 2 mil leitos de UTI para tratar pacientes com Covid-19|website=Infomoney|date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322095100/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/sus-preve-2-mil-leitos-de-uti-para-tratar-pacientes-com-covid-19.ghtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, second cases were confirmed in Esp\u00edrito Santo<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.agazeta.com.br/es/gv/entenda-como-esta-a-situacao-do-coronavirus-no-es-e-no-mundo-0320|title=Entenda como est\u00e1 a situa\u00e7\u00e3o do coronav\u00edrus no ES e no mundo|website=agazeta.com.br|language=pt-br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320024123/https://www.agazeta.com.br/es/gv/entenda-como-esta-a-situacao-do-coronavirus-no-es-e-no-mundo-0320|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and Minas Gerais.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/12/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-e-confirmado-em-minas-gerais-diz-governo-do-estado.ghtml|title=Segundo caso de coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 confirmado em Minas Gerais, diz governo do estado|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320024121/https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/12/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-e-confirmado-em-minas-gerais-diz-governo-do-estado.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \nAlso on 12 March, the cruise ship ''[[Silver Shadow (ship)|Silver Shadow]]'' from [[the Bahamas]] with 318 passengers and 291 crew members, docked in [[Recife]], Pernambuco, with a suspected case of COVID-19 in a 78-year-old Canadian tourist. The ship was isolated by health authorities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/nahorah/cruzeiro-fica-em-quarentena-em-recife-apos-idoso-ser-suspeito-de-contrair-coronavirus|title=Cruzeiro fica em quarentena em Recife ap\u00f3s idoso ser suspeito de contrair coronav\u00edrus|website=Jornal de Bras\u00edlia|date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, President Jair Bolsonaro tested negative for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/13/coronavirus-bolsonaro-testa-negativo-diz-perfil-do-presidente-no-facebook.htm|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Bolsonaro testa negativo para covid-19|website=UOL|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140808/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/13/coronavirus-bolsonaro-testa-negativo-diz-perfil-do-presidente-no-facebook.htm|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://time.com/5802494/jair-bolsonaro-brazil-coronavirus|title=Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro Tests Negative for Coronavirus|website=Time|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313191155/https://time.com/5802494/jair-bolsonaro-brazil-coronavirus/|archive-date=13 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]] reported its first case \u2013 becoming the first state in the [[North Region, Brazil|North Region]] to do so \u2014, while [[Goi\u00e1s]] (in the Central-West Region) reported its first three cases, with 25 new cases being confirmed nationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-13-de-marco.ghtml|title=13 March report|website=G1|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314164519/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-13-de-marco.ghtml|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The Ministry of Health issued a warning recommending Brazilians and foreigners arriving in Brazil to stay in isolation for at least 7 days.><ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/ministerio-da-saude-divulga-orientacoes-para-estados-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade recomenda que viajante internacional fique em casa por 7 dias ao chegar ao Brasil|website=G1|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314134057/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/ministerio-da-saude-divulga-orientacoes-para-estados-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Also on 13 March, the first patient of COVID-19 in the country, the 61-year-old man from S\u00e3o Paulo, finally recovered.<ref>{{cite web|title=Governo anuncia que primeiro paciente com coronav\u00edrus no Brasil est\u00e1 curado|url=https://istoe.com.br/governo-anuncia-que-primeiro-paciente-com-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-curado/|date=13 March 2020|language=pt-BR|accessdate=14 March 2020|publisher=Isto\u00e9|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316063738/https://istoe.com.br/governo-anuncia-que-primeiro-paciente-com-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-curado/|archive-date=16 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, Brazil confirmed 23 additional cases. [[Mato Grosso do Sul]] (in the Central-West Region) and [[Sergipe]] (in the Northeast) reported their first cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/14/brasil-tem-121-casos-de-coronavirus-segundo-relatorio-do-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 121 casos de coronav\u00edrus, segundo relat\u00f3rio do Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320031450/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/14/brasil-tem-121-casos-de-coronavirus-segundo-relatorio-do-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sc/santa-catarina/noticia/2020/03/14/sc-tem-1a-transmissao-local-do-novo-coronavirus-casos-da-doenca-no-estado-chegam-a-5.ghtml|title=SC tem 1\u00aa transmiss\u00e3o local do novo coronav\u00edrus; casos da doen\u00e7a no estado chegam a 5|website=G1|date=13 March 2020|access-date=14 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315165417/https://g1.globo.com/sc/santa-catarina/noticia/2020/03/14/sc-tem-1a-transmissao-local-do-novo-coronavirus-casos-da-doenca-no-estado-chegam-a-5.ghtml|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariodepernambuco.com.br/noticia/vidaurbana/2020/03/pernambuco-tem-sete-casos-confirmados-e-ja-registra-transmissao-local.html|title=Pernambuco tem sete casos confirmados e j\u00e1 registra transmiss\u00e3o local do Covid-19|website=Di\u00e1rio de Pernambuco|date=14 March 2020|access-date=14 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317191804/https://www.diariodepernambuco.com.br/noticia/vidaurbana/2020/03/pernambuco-tem-sete-casos-confirmados-e-ja-registra-transmissao-local.html|archive-date=17 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, Brazil confirmed 43 additional cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/15/brasil-tem-176-casos-de-coronavirus-segundo-relatorio-do-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 200 casos confirmados|website=G1|date=15 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316101245/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/15/brasil-tem-176-casos-de-coronavirus-segundo-relatorio-do-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|archive-date=16 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> That same day, President Jair Bolsonaro, who was being monitored by doctors after Wajngarten tested positive for COVID-19, was heavily criticized for meeting his supporters in a public parade in Bras\u00edlia without wearing a mask.<ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://www.canalrural.com.br/radar/bolsonaro-tira-selfies-com-manifestantes-em-frente-ao-palacio-do-planalto-2/|title=Bolsonaro tira selfies com manifestantes em frente ao Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322033033/https://www.canalrural.com.br/radar/bolsonaro-tira-selfies-com-manifestantes-em-frente-ao-palacio-do-planalto-2/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===16\u201331 March===\nOn 16 March, Brazil confirmed 34 additional cases, totaling 234, the largest number in [[Latin America]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus|title=Notifica\u00e7\u00e3o de casos de doen\u00e7a pelo Coronav\u00edrus 2019|website=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=16 March 2020|access-date=4 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227111830/http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, the first coronavirus-related death was confirmed in the country. It was a 62-year-old man hospitalized in a private hospital in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/sao-paulo-registra-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.shtml|title=S\u00e3o Paulo registra primeira morte por coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S.Paulo|date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318140829/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/sao-paulo-registra-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.shtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, the [[Ministry of Health]] reported 291 confirmed cases in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|title=Notifica\u00e7\u00e3o de casos de doen\u00e7a pelo coronav\u00edrus 2019 (COVID-19) \u2013 Plataforma Integrada de Vigil\u00e2ncia em Sa\u00fade \u2013 Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=18 March 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200318192904/http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|archive-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Brazil confirmed three additional deaths. The patients were a 65-year-old man, an 85-year-old man (both with pre-existing conditions), and an 80-year-old man (without pre-existing conditions); they were all from the state of S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/sp-registra-mais-duas-mortes-por-coronavirus-total-vai-a-3.ghtml|title=SP registra mais duas mortes por coronav\u00edrus; total vai a 3|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318183455/https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/sp-registra-mais-duas-mortes-por-coronavirus-total-vai-a-3.ghtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/sp-tem-quatro-mortes-confirmadas-pelo-coronavirus.ghtml|title=SP confirma quatro mortes pelo coronav\u00edrus no estado|website=G1|language=pt-br|date=18 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318234211/https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/sp-tem-quatro-mortes-confirmadas-pelo-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> That same day, [[Par\u00e1]] (in the North) reported its first confirmed case. The patient, a 37-year-old person from [[Bel\u00e9m]], is quarantined with his family.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/pa/para/noticia/2020/03/18/secretaria-estadual-de-saude-confirma-primeiro-caso-de-coronavirus-no-para.ghtml|title=Secretaria Estadual de Sa\u00fade confirma primeiro caso de coronav\u00edrus no Par\u00e1|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318195223/https://g1.globo.com/pa/para/noticia/2020/03/18/secretaria-estadual-de-saude-confirma-primeiro-caso-de-coronavirus-no-para.ghtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Also on 18 March, President Jair Bolsonaro confirmed that two of his Ministers ([[Bento Costa Lima|Bento Albuquerque]] and [[Augusto Heleno]]) had tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/18/com-mascaras-bolsonaro-e-ministros-fazem-pronunciamento-sobre-coronavirus-no-planalto.ghtml|title=Em entrevista sobre coronav\u00edrus, Bolsonaro diz que governo ganha 'de goleada' e pede elogios|website=G1}}</ref> At night, he once again made a televised address to the nation, which was met with ''[[Cacerolazo|panela\u00e7os]]'' from both his followers and opponents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/18/sao-paulo-rio-recife-belo-horizonte-e-fortaleza-registram-panelacos-durante-pronunciamento-de-jair-bolsonaro.ghtml|title=Cidades registram panela\u00e7os contra Bolsonaro durante e depois de pronunciamento|website=G1|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320050450/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/18/sao-paulo-rio-recife-belo-horizonte-e-fortaleza-registram-panelacos-durante-pronunciamento-de-jair-bolsonaro.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> By the end of the night, the Ministry of Health had reported 428 cases in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46558-coronavirus-4-mortes-e-428-casos-confirmados|language=pt-br|title=ATEN\u00c7\u00c3O! Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade atualiza situa\u00e7\u00e3o sobre o coronav\u00edrus por meio de coletiva online|website=saude.gov.br|date=19 March 2020|trans-title=ATTENTION! Ministry of Health updates situation on coronavirus through online conference|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319014945/https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46558-coronavirus-4-mortes-e-428-casos-confirmados|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBy 19 March, Brazil had seven deaths from COVID-19. The first death in the state of Rio de Janeiro was that of a 63-year-old domestic worker from [[Miguel Pereira, Rio de Janeiro|Miguel Pereira]] who was not warned of the risk of contagion by her employer, who was infected with coronavirus in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/brasil/2020-03-19/primeira-morte-do-rio-domestica-nao-foi-avisada-de-risco-de-contagio-por-patroa.html|title=Dom\u00e9stica morta n\u00e3o foi avisada de risco de cont\u00e1gio por 'patroa' \u2013 Brasil \u2013 iG|first=Ag\u00eancia|last=P\u00fablica|date=19 March 2020|website=\u00daltimo Segundo|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319221705/https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/brasil/2020-03-19/primeira-morte-do-rio-domestica-nao-foi-avisada-de-risco-de-contagio-por-patroa.html|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/19/rj-confirma-a-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RJ confirma a primeira morte por coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319160651/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/19/rj-confirma-a-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The other victims were a 69-year-old man from [[Niter\u00f3i]], who was [[Diabetes|diabetic]] and [[Hypertension|hypertensive]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-do-rj-confirma-a-segunda-morte-por-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RJ confirma a segunda morte por coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319160610/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-do-rj-confirma-a-segunda-morte-por-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and an unidentified person hospitalized in a private hospital in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://istoe.com.br/hospital-confirma-mais-uma-morte-por-coronavirus-em-sp-total-no-pais-chega-a-7/|title=Hospital confirma mais uma morte por coronav\u00edrus em SP; total no Pa\u00eds chega a 7|website=Isto\u00e9|language=pt-br|access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref> According to [[G1 (website)|G1]], there were 647 confirmed cases in the country by night.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/19/brasil-tem-621-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 621 casos de coronav\u00edrus e transmiss\u00e3o sustentada muda atendimento em postos, diz minist\u00e9rio|website=G1|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320141547/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/19/brasil-tem-621-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBy 20 March, Brazil had 11 deaths from COVID-19. The four new victims were a 70-year-old man, an 80-year-old man, a 93-year-old man and an 83-year-old woman. All of them had pre-existing conditions and were hospitalized in private hospitals in the state of S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jornaldafronteira.com.br/foi-confirmada-a-oitava-morte-por-coronavirus-no-brasil/|title=Foi confirmada a oitava morte por Coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|first=Ana|last=Carolina|date=20 March 2020}}</ref> The number of confirmed cases reached 904.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-tem-11-mortes-por-covid-19-e-904-casos-confirmados-20032020|title=Brasil tem 11 mortes por covid-19 e 904 casos confirmados|date=20 March 2020|website=R7.com|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321165114/https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-tem-11-mortes-por-covid-19-e-904-casos-confirmados-20032020|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ultimas-noticias-de-coronavirus-de-20-de-marco.ghtml|title=\u00daltimas not\u00edcias de coronav\u00edrus de 20 de mar\u00e7o|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182401/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ultimas-noticias-de-coronavirus-de-20-de-marco.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In two hours, the number of confirmed cases in the country went from 750 to 970.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://24horas.com.br/brasil/governo-declara-transmissao-comunitaria-do-covid-19-em-todo-pais/|title=Governo declara transmiss\u00e3o comunit\u00e1ria de coronav\u00edrus em todo o Brasil|date=20 March 2020}}</ref> By night, the health departments of the Brazilian states had reported 977 confirmed cases. COVID-19 cases were confirmed in 23 states and the Federal District.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/casos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-20-de-marco.ghtml|title=Casos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil em 20 de mar\u00e7o|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321010341/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/casos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-20-de-marco.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Brazil had 18 deaths from COVID-19. By noon, the health departments had reported 1,000 confirmed. Rio de Janeiro confirmed its third death. The victim was a 65-year-old man from [[Petr\u00f3polis]]. According to ''[[Folha de S. Paulo]]'', he had been hospitalized in a private hospital since returning from a trip to [[Egypt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/21/ultimas-noticias-de-coronavirus-de-21-de-marco.ghtml|title=\u00daltimas not\u00edcias de coronav\u00edrus de 21 de mar\u00e7o|website=G1|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321115936/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/21/ultimas-noticias-de-coronavirus-de-21-de-marco.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffpostbrasil.com/entry/morte-rio-coronavirus_br_5e762d4ac5b6eab77949048c|title=Rio confirma 3\u00ba morte pelo novo coronav\u00edrus; s\u00e3o 12 v\u00edtimas no Brasil|date=21 March 2020|website=HuffPost Brasil}}</ref> \nS\u00e3o Paulo, in turn, reported six additional deaths: four women (aged 89, 76, 73, and 89), and two men (aged 90, and 49). S\u00e3o Paulo is the focus of the disease in the country, with 459 confirmed cases. As such, the local government has declared a state-wide quarantine starting on 24 March. The measure determined the closure of all commerce and non-essential services from that date until 7 April. By the end of the day, 1,128 cases were confirmed by the ministry of Health in 25 states and the Federal District.<ref name=\"exame\">{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/|title=Brasil tem 1546 casos e 25 mortes pelo coronav\u00edrus|website=EXAME|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319232448/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n[[Maranh\u00e3o]] (in the Northeast) reported its first case. Only the state of [[Roraima]] (in The North) was the last to register a COVID-19 case, so all states and the Federal District registered cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.em.com.br/app/noticia/nacional/2020/03/21/interna_nacional,1131117/sao-paulo-registra-mais-seis-mortes-por-coronavirus-agora-ja-sao-18-n.shtml|title=S\u00e3o Paulo registra mais seis mortes por coronav\u00edrus; agora j\u00e1 s\u00e3o 18 no pa\u00eds \u2013 Nacional \u2013 Estado de Minas|first1=Estado de|last1=Minas|first2=Estado de|last2=Minas|date=21 March 2020|website=Estado de Minas|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321171215/https://www.em.com.br/app/noticia/nacional/2020/03/21/interna_nacional,1131117/sao-paulo-registra-mais-seis-mortes-por-coronavirus-agora-ja-sao-18-n.shtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/21/numero-de-mortes-por-coronavirus-em-sp-sobe-para-15-segundo-governo-do-estado.ghtml|title=N\u00famero de mortes por coronav\u00edrus no estado de SP sobe para 15; s\u00e3o 459 casos confirmados|website=G1|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321160152/https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/21/numero-de-mortes-por-coronavirus-em-sp-sobe-para-15-segundo-governo-do-estado.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tupi.fm/coronavirus/brasil-ja-tem-18-mortos-por-novo-coronavirus/|title=Brasil j\u00e1 tem 18 mortos por novo coronav\u00edrus|date=21 March 2020|website=Super R\u00e1dio Tupi|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321171215/https://www.tupi.fm/coronavirus/brasil-ja-tem-18-mortos-por-novo-coronavirus/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, Brazil had 25 deaths from COVID-19. The Ministry of Health reported on Sunday (22) that the number of confirmed cases of covid-19 \u2013 the disease caused by the new coronavirus \u2013 reached 1,546. The death toll from the disease has grown to 25 people, according to the ministry. \n[[S\u00e3o Paulo]] continues to concentrate the number of cases in the country. There are 631 records. The number of fatalities in the state has already reached 22, according to the ministry's balance sheet. All took place in the city of S\u00e3o Paulo. Thus, the percentage of fatal cases is 3.5%. Of the seven new deaths confirmed since yesterday, five are men (76, 81, 82, 82, 83 years old) and two are women (88 and 96 years old). Among the total deaths recorded so far, 21 occurred in private hospitals and one in a public hospital.\nIn the State of [[Rio de Janeiro]], the number of cases is 186 and there are three deaths in the cities of [[Niter\u00f3i]], [[Petr\u00f3polis]] and [[Miguel Pereira, Rio de Janeiro|Miguel Pereira]], which is equivalent to a lethality rate of 1.6%. In less than 24 hours, the city of Rio de Janeiro registered a 60.5% increase in the number of confirmed cases of the new coronavirus in the capital. In a bulletin released at 2&nbsp;pm, 170 notifications were recorded. Of this total, 23 people are hospitalized, 12 in ICUs. There are still 175 suspected cases. There are no confirmed deaths in the state capital.\n[[Roraima]], which was the only state with no cases registered until Saturday, accounts for two occurrences. Thus, all units of the Brazilian Federation already have Covid-19 records.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-registra-1546-casos-e-25-mortes-por-covid-19-diz-ministerio-22032020|title=Brasil registra 1.546 casos e 25 mortes por covid-19, diz minist\u00e9rio|date=22 March 2020|website=R7.com|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322212836/https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-registra-1546-casos-e-25-mortes-por-covid-19-diz-ministerio-22032020|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/coronavirus-brasil-tem-1546-casos-25-mortes-segundo-ministerio-da-saude-24321632|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Brasil tem 1.546 casos e 25 mortes, segundo Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=22 March 2020|website=O Globo|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322214025/https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/coronavirus-brasil-tem-1546-casos-25-mortes-segundo-ministerio-da-saude-24321632|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nIn [[Bahia]], confirmed by SESAB, there are already 55 confirmed cases, 33 in [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], seven in [[Porto Seguro]], six in [[Feira de Santana]], three in [[Lauro de Freitas]], and two in [[Prado]]. The cities that have only one confirmed case are [[Itabuna]], [[Cama\u00e7ari]], and more recently registered, [[Barreiras]] and [[Concei\u00e7\u00e3o do Jacu\u00edpe]]. Across the country there are already 1604 infected and 25 deaths registered.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ilheusnoticias.com.br/2020/03/23/novo-balanco-de-notificacoes-suspeitas-de-covid-19-em-itabuna-e-divulgado-pela-vigilancia-epidemiologica/|title=Novo balan\u00e7o de notifica\u00e7\u00f5es suspeitas de Covid-19 em Itabuna \u00e9 divulgado pela Vigil\u00e2ncia Epidemiol\u00f3gica|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323021817/https://ilheusnoticias.com.br/2020/03/23/novo-balanco-de-notificacoes-suspeitas-de-covid-19-em-itabuna-e-divulgado-pela-vigilancia-epidemiologica/|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, Brazil had 34 deaths from COVID-19. New number of patients represents an increase of 22% in relation to the 1,546 cases registered until Sunday (22). Among deaths, growth was 36%. The total number of confirmed cases of a new coronavirus (Sars-Cov-2) rose to 1,891 on Monday (23), according to a balance by the [[Ministry of Health]]. The number of deaths also increased to 34 deaths.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://s2.glbimg.com/PDXsoIIIN-UjJC6nroWRBLoe3Xo=/0x0:1200x3522/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/Z/U/BSd7r8T0KEhhczA9aAfg/mapa-brasil-casos-coronavirus2303.png |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324090410/https://s2.glbimg.com/PDXsoIIIN-UjJC6nroWRBLoe3Xo%3D/0x0:1200x3522/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/Z/U/BSd7r8T0KEhhczA9aAfg/mapa-brasil-casos-coronavirus2303.png |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/23/brasil-tem-1891-casos-e-34-mortes-por-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |title=Coronav\u00edrus: Brasil tem 34 mortes e 1.891 casos confirmados, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323203611/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/23/brasil-tem-1891-casos-e-34-mortes-por-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, Brazil had 46 deaths from COVID-19. According to the [[Ministry of Health]], this Tuesday (24) Brazil registers 2201 people infected with the coronavirus and 46 dead. [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] is the state that leads the list with 910 cases and 40 deaths, followed by [[Rio de Janeiro]], which records 305 cases and 6 deaths. And more: Elderly residents of communities will be hosted in hotels in Rio de Janeiros to avoid contamination.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/jr-24h/boletim-jr-24h/videos/brasil-tem-46-mortos-e-2201-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-24032020|title=Brasil tem 46 mortos e 2201 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus|date=24 March 2020|website=R7.com|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, Brazil had 57 deaths from COVID-19. The number of confirmed cases of coronavirus (Covid-19) in Brazil rose to 2,433, according to information passed by the states to the [[Ministry of Health]] on Wednesday (25). To date, there are 57 deaths, 48 in the state of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] and six in [[Rio de Janeiro]]. The [[North]], [[Northeast]] and [[South]] regions recorded the first deaths, one in [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], one in [[Pernambuco]] and one in [[Rio Grande do Sul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46600-coronavirus-57-mortes-e-2-433-casos-confirmados|title= Coronav\u00edrus: 57 mortes e 2.433 casos confirmados |website=saude.gov.br |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, Brazil had 77 deaths from COVID-19. One month after the first case of coronavirus (causing Covid-19 disease) in Brazil, confirmed on 26 February, the country has 2,915 infected and 77 deaths. The lethality rate is 2.7%. The balance was released by the [[Ministry of Health]], on Thursday, 26. The first death in Brazil was registered on 17 March, in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]. The state has already registered more than 90% of cases but now it is almost 40%, with 1,052 infected. Despite this, it still has the highest number of deaths, 58. There are also deaths in [[Rio de Janeiro]] (9), [[Goi\u00e1s]] (1), [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]] (1), [[Rio Grande do Sul]] (1), [[Cear\u00e1]] (3), [[Pernambuco]] ( 3) and [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]] (1). In addition to [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], the states with the most infections are: [[Rio de Janeiro]] (421), [[Cear\u00e1]] (235) and the [[Federal District]] (200).<ref>{{cite web | url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/ |title = Mortes no Brasil por coronav\u00edrus sobem 19% em um dia e chegam a 92}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, Brazil had 92 deaths from COVID-19. The [[Ministry of Health]] released the most recent balance of cases of Covid-19, a disease caused by the coronavirus Sars-Cov-2. The main figures are: 92 deaths, 3,417 confirmed cases, 2.7% is the fatality rate. [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] concentrates 1,223 cases, and [[Rio de Janeiro]], 493. According to the Ministry of Health, until 3 pm, there were 116 patients admitted to wards and another 148 patients in the ICU. The numbers only consider people whose test results have already been presented and tested positive. Disregard suspected cases.<ref>https://s2.glbimg.com/eZMLfm7bBIcgDfImgVOxLmotA4k=/0x0:1200x3522/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/y/3/3cbi9xRXKkEsucG1ubkQ/mapa-brasil-casos-coronavirus2703.png</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/27/brasil-tem-92-mortes-e-3417-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 92 mortes e 3.417 casos confirmados de novo coronav\u00edrus, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|website=G1}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, Brazil had 117 deaths from COVID-19. The Ministry of Health reported on Saturday (28) that Brazil has so far registered 114 deaths and 3,904 confirmed cases of coronavirus. The mortality of Covid-19 in the country is 2.9%, according to the balance released by the folder. The survey also points out that, in the country, men die more from coronavirus than women \u2013 61.4% (H) against 38.6% (M). Approximately 90% of deaths are people over 60 years of age. In 84% of deaths, patients had at least one risk factor. The most common, according to the Ministry, is heart disease, followed by diabetes and [[pneumopathy]]. According to the folder, the state with the highest number of cases is [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], with 1,406. Then, [[Rio de Janeiro]] with 558. Then, [[Cear\u00e1]], 314. The southeast region concentrates 56.9% of cases in Brazil, followed by [[northeast]] (16%), [[south]] (13.2%) centerwest (9.2%) %) and [[north]] (4.7%). Of the 22 deaths added to the total in the country this Saturday, the state of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] had 16 deaths. Two more dead were confirmed in the state, but not yet accounted for by the secretariat and the Ministry of Health: a 56-year-old student in the Chemistry course at [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo|USP]] and a 26-year-old who died at Hospital Santa Cruz, in [[Vila Mariana (district of S\u00e3o Paulo)|Vila Mariana]], S\u00e3o Paulo. . With them, there are already 86 deaths in SP. In addition to them, the Health Department of [[Rio Grande do Norte]] confirmed late Saturday night the first death from the new coronavirus in the state. The victim is a 61-year-old [[university]] professor with a history of [[diabetes]]. With this case there are 117 deaths in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-tem-114-mortes-e-3904-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-28032020|title=Brasil tem 114 mortes e 3.904 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus|date=28 March 2020|website=R7.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/28/brasil-tem-111-mortes-e-3904-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 114 mortes e 3.904 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|website=G1}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/28/jovem-de-26-anos-morre-com-coronavirus-em-sp-diz-hospital.ghtml|title=Jovem de 26 anos morre com coronav\u00edrus em SP, diz hospital|website=G1}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 March, Brazil had 136 deaths from COVID-19. The [[Ministry of Health]] released on Sunday (29) the most recent balance of cases of Covid-19, a disease caused by the coronavirus Sars-Cov-2. The main figures are: 136 deaths, 4,256 confirmed cases and the lethality rate rose from 2.8% until Saturday (28) to 3.2% this Sunday. The state of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] concentrates 1,451 cases and the [[Rio de Janeiro]] 600 cases. The balance added 22 deaths to the total. In the balance of the previous day, Brazil had 114 deaths. This represents a 19% increase in the number of deaths. Sunday saw the same increase in the number of deaths as Saturday, where there were also 22 more victims. These are the two days with the highest number of deaths in Brazil from the new coronavirus so far. The highest rates came from [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] (98 deaths) and [[Rio de Janeiro]] (17 deaths). In addition, deaths from covid-19 were recorded in [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]] (1), [[Bahia]] (1), [[Cear\u00e1]] (5), [[Pernambuco]] (5), [[Piau\u00ed]] (1), [[Rio Grande do Norte]] (1), [[Federal District]] (1), [[Goi\u00e1s]] (1), [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]] (2), [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]] (1) and [[Rio Grande do Sul]] (2). Among the 136 deaths, 98 occurred in the state of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]. There was an increase of 14 deaths in SP in the balance of this Sunday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/29/brasil-tem-136-mortes-e-4256-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 136 mortes e 4.256 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|website=G1}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/03/29/brasil-registra-136-mortes-decorrentes-do-novo-coronavirus-em-24-horas.htm|title=Brasil registra 4.256 casos e 136 mortes decorrentes do novo coronav\u00edrus|website=noticias.uol.com.br}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, Brazil had 159 deaths from COVID-19. The number of deaths due to the new coronavirus (covid-19) rose from 136 to 159 between yesterday and today. An increase of 16% between the last update and the one just released by the [[Ministry of Health]]. Confirmed cases, on the other hand, went from 4,256 to 4,579. The result of new 323 infected people marked an increase of 7% compared to yesterday. The number was the lowest performance in the last five days, when the number of new people infected, for example, surpassed 500 last Friday (27). The states with the most cases were [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] (1451), [[Rio de Janeiro]] (600), [[Cear\u00e1]] (372), [[Distrito Federal]] (312) and [[Minas Gerais]] (231). The lowest incidence is in states in the North Region, such as [[Rond\u00f4nia]] (6), [[Amap\u00e1]] (8), [[Tocantins]] (9) and [[Roraima]] (16). The lethality index reached 3.5% with today's balance, above the one seen in yesterday's balance, when it was around 3.2%. In [[Mato Grosso do Sul]] there is no record of deaths. But there are already 44 people with the coronavirus and another 51 under investigation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.enfoquems.com.br/noticias/brasil-registra-4579-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-e-159-mortes-da-doenca|title=Brasil registra 4.579 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus e 159 mortes da doen\u00e7a|website=Enfoque MS - Not\u00edcias de Campo Grande/MS}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, Brazil had 201 deaths from COVID-19. The number of deaths due to the new coronavirus reached 201, this Tuesday (31). The number of new deaths, 42, was the highest in the historical series. The highest number of deaths in a day so far had been 23, yesterday (30). The result marks an increase of 26% in relation to the previous day, when 159 deaths were registered. Regarding the profile, 41.4% were women and 68.6%, men. Regarding age, 89% were over 60 years old. Regarding health complications, most (107) had [[heart]] disease, 75 had [[diabetes]], 33 [[pneumopathy]] and 22 some [[neurological]] condition. The deaths occurred in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] (136), [[Rio de Janeiro]] (23), [[Cear\u00e1]] (7), [[Pernambuco]] (6), [[Piau\u00ed]] (4), [[Rio Grande do Sul]] (4), [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]] (3), [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]] (3), [[Federal District]] (3), [[Minas Gerais]] (2), [[Bahia]] (2), [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]] (2), [[Alagoas]] (1), [[Maranh\u00e3o]] (1), [[Goi\u00e1s]] (1), [[Rond\u00f4nia]] (1) and [[Rio Grande do Norte]] (1) .\nThe confirmed cases went from 4,579 to 5,717. The result of new 1,138 people infected in one day was more than double the highest recorded so far, of 502 new cases on March 27. The states with the most cases are [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] (2,339), [[Rio de Janeiro]] (708), [[Cear\u00e1]] (390), [[Distrito Federal]] (332) and [[Minas Gerais]] (275). The lowest incidence is in states in the Northern Region, such as [[Rond\u00f4nia]] (eight), [[Amap\u00e1]] (10), [[Tocantins]] (11) and [[Roraima]] (16). The lethality rate, which was below 2% at the weekend, was 3.5% on today's balance sheet, the same as recorded yesterday. Hospitalizations went from 757 yesterday to 1,075 today.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/saude/noticia/2020-03/ao-vivo-pais-tem-201-obitos-por-covid-e-5717-casos-confirmados|title=Pa\u00eds tem 201 mortes por covid-19 e 5.717 casos confirmados|date=31 March 2020|website=Ag\u00eancia Brasil}}</ref>\n\n===1\u201315 April===\nOn 31 March, Brazil had 241 deaths from COVID-19. The [[Ministry of Health]] released on Wednesday (1st) the most recent national assessment of the cases of Covid-19, a disease caused by the coronavirus Sars-Cov-2. The main data are: 241 deaths, 6,836 confirmed cases, 3.5% is the fatality rate. Among more than 200 deaths analyzed, 89% were of people over 60 and 84% of people with at least one comorbidity, which is a pre-existing disease. Seven of the 212 deaths analyzed occurred in people under the age of 60 and without comorbidities. The deaths are located in the states of [[Amazonas]] (3), [[Par\u00e1]] (1), [[Rond\u00f4nia]] (1), [[Alagoas]] (1), [[Bahia]] (2), [[Cear\u00e1]] (8), [[Maranh\u00e3o]] (1), [[Para\u00edba]] (1), [[Pernambuco]] (8) ), [[Piau\u00ed]] (4), [[Rio Grande do Norte]] (2), [[Minas Gerais]] (3), [[Rio de Janeiro]] (28), [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] (164), [[Federal District]] (3), [[Goi\u00e1s]] (1), [[Mato Grosso do Sul]] ( 1), [[Paran\u00e1]] (3), [[Rio Grande do Sul]] (4) and [[Santa Catarina]] (2). All Brazilian regions have confirmed cases of deaths from coronavirus. Only the states of [[Acre]], [[Amap\u00e1]], [[Roraima]], [[Tocantins]], [[Sergipe]], [[Esp\u00edrito Santo]] and [[Mato Grosso]] do not have confirmed deaths from the disease so far, but they also register confirmed cases, as do all other Brazilian states.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46637-brasil-registra-6-836-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-e-241-mortes|title= Brasil registra 6.836 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus e 241 mortes  |website=saude.gov.br |date= 1 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/04/01/brasil-tem-240-mortes-e-6836-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 241 mortes e 6.836 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus; ministro diz que n\u00famero \u00e9 maior|website=G1}}</ref>\n\n==Response==\nPolicy responses and prevention announced in the country amid the Covid-19 pandemic.\n\n[[File:Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade - Livreto Plano de Contingencia Covid-19 Coronavirus 2020.pdf|thumb|Contingency plan booklet of the pandemic]]\n\n===Scientific research and forecast===\n\n[[File:SARS-CoV-2 without background.png|thumb|Illustration of the [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]] ]]\n\nOn 28 February, [[researchers]] from [[Brazil]] and the [[University of Oxford]] [[sequenced]] the 2019 n-CoV virus [[genome]] from the first confirmed case of the disease in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]. The work, usually done in 15 days by scientists, was done in just two days, according to the [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] State Research Support Foundation ([[Fapesp]]). The first preliminary analysis by the scientists shows that the genome of the coronavirus diagnosed in Brazil differs in three points in the genetic code of the virus found initially in [[Wuhan]], the Chinese city where the disease arose. According to one of the study's authors, Ester Cerdeira Sabino, the more we unravel the virus's [[RNA]], the more we can track its path.\n\n[[Genetic analysis]] of a virus's [[RNA]] is also essential for the development of [[vaccines]] and the creation of [[diagnostic]] tests. A preliminary analysis of the sequence is now available online for consultation by other researchers worldwide. The research was carried out by the Adolfo Lutz Institute in partnership with the Institute of Tropical Medicine of the [[Faculty of Medicine]] of the [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]] and the [[University of Oxford]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/cientistas-do-brasil-e-de-oxford-sequenciam-genoma-do-novo-coronavirus-detectado-em-sp.ghtml |title=Cientistas do Brasil e de Oxford sequenciam genoma do novo coronav\u00edrus detectado em SP &#124; Coronav\u00edrus &#124; G1 |publisher=G1.globo.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, Scientists predict up to 2 million deaths in Brazil in the worst scenario without measures to contain the virus. They point out that a policy of [[social distancing]] is one of the most effective measures without a [[vaccine]].<ref name=\"auto10\">{{cite web|url=https://www.opovo.com.br/coronavirus/2020/03/19/cientistas-prevem-ate-2-milhoes-de-mortes-no-brasil-no-pior-cenario-sem-medidas-para-conter-o-virus.html|title=Cientistas prevem at\u00e9 2 milh\u00f5es de mortes no Brasil no pior cen\u00e1rio sem medidas para conter o v\u00edrus|first=O.|last=Povo|date=21 March 2020|website=Coronavirus|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320142716/https://www.opovo.com.br/coronavirus/2020/03/19/cientistas-prevem-ate-2-milhoes-de-mortes-no-brasil-no-pior-cenario-sem-medidas-para-conter-o-virus.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, experts from Italy warned that the Coronavirus growth curve in Brazil would repeat that of European countries. Observatory with physicists from University of S\u00e3o Paulo [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo|USP]], [[Unicamp]], [[Unesp]], [[UnB]], [[UFABC]], Berkley (US) and Oldenburg (Germany) shows that the number of infected people, considering data from March 19th, had been doubling every 54 hours, and that the case Total would exceed 3 thousand on the 24th.<ref name=\"auto13\">{{cite web|url=https://epocanegocios.globo.com/Mundo/noticia/2020/03/curva-de-crescimento-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-repete-de-paises-europeus-alertam-especialistas-da-italia.html|title=Curva de crescimento do coronav\u00edrus no Brasil repete a de pa\u00edses europeus, alertam especialistas da It\u00e1lia|website=\u00c9poca Neg\u00f3cios|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320183307/https://epocanegocios.globo.com/Mundo/noticia/2020/03/curva-de-crescimento-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-repete-de-paises-europeus-alertam-especialistas-da-italia.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ritmo-de-contagio-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-igual-ao-registrado-na-italia-e-acelerando-aponta-unesp.ghtml|title=Ritmo de cont\u00e1gio do coronav\u00edrus no Brasil est\u00e1 igual ao registrado na It\u00e1lia e acelerando, apontam universidades|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173906/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ritmo-de-contagio-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-igual-ao-registrado-na-italia-e-acelerando-aponta-unesp.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn March 21th, researchers are mobilizing to increase test availability in Brazil. The expectation is that with just a drop of blood from the patient it will be possible to know if he has the new coronavirus and at what stage; the idea is that experiments are ready for the current wave of COVID-19 and action mobilizes some of the main Brazilian universities.<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/pesquisadores-se-mobilizam-para-aumentar-oferta-de-testes-no-brasil,d6a76c837c86a20c120e5d733d51a3ebrddc3q94.html|title=Pesquisadores se mobilizam para aumentar oferta de testes no Brasil|website=Terra|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163919/https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/pesquisadores-se-mobilizam-para-aumentar-oferta-de-testes-no-brasil,d6a76c837c86a20c120e5d733d51a3ebrddc3q94.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nThe [[Health Minister]] has said the numbers will increase exponentially until the end of June.<ref name=\"exame\"/>\n\nOn March 22nd, Brazil reached a thousand cases after Italy and Spain. A [[North American University]] survey shows that the evolution of the disease in the country is slower than that observed elsewhere. Brazil took longer to go from 100 to 1,000 cases of COVID-19 than countries like Italy and Spain. The data used were compiled by the American university Johns Hopkins. The country passed 100 confirmed cases of the new coronavirus on March 13th. That day, 151 cases were recorded. Eight days later, on March 21st, Brazil reached the 1,000th positive test and reached 1,021 people with the disease. In Italy, this movement took place between February 23rd and 29th (six days); in Spain, between March 2nd and 9th  (seven days). This means, in the assessment of a statistical expert in epidemiology, Antonio Ponce de Leon, that the rate of infections in Brazil is slower. Italy and Spain are the European countries most affected by the virus. The first recorded, March 22nd, more than 59 thousand cases and 5.4 thousand deaths. Spain had 28,700 patients with 1,700 deaths. Both, who had their health systems collapsed because of the disease, started the fight by restricting the tests to only the most serious cases \u2013 the same Brazilian strategy. The justification was that this was a finite and expensive resource.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/brasil/2020-03-23/coronavirus-brasil-demorou-mais-que-italia-e-espanha-para-atingir-mil-casos.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324092849/https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/brasil/2020-03-23/coronavirus-brasil-demorou-mais-que-italia-e-espanha-para-atingir-mil-casos.html |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, Research predicts a negative GDP of up to 4.4% with the effect of the coronavirus. The study makes a projection of the impact on the economy, comparing to the effects of the crisis of 2008 and the strike of truck drivers in 2018. The impact of the coronavirus will come through two channels: an external channel and the domestic channel. With the pandemic, the [[Economy of the United States|American economy]], the European economy and the [[Chinese economy]] have practically stopped, or are in a very strong deceleration rhythm. With that, by itself, it would already have a very strong effect in Brazil without a doubt.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://noticias.r7.com/economia/pesquisa-preve-pib-negativo-de-ate-44-com-efeito-do-coronavirus-23032020 |title=Pesquisa prev\u00ea PIB negativo de at\u00e9 4,4% com efeito do coronav\u00edrus |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095828/https://noticias.r7.com/economia/pesquisa-preve-pib-negativo-de-ate-44-com-efeito-do-coronavirus-23032020 |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, The increase in demand and the lack of [[protective masks]] in the market for [[health professionals]] who are at the forefront of combating the new coronavirus ([[covid-19]]) brought together several researchers and students from universities in [[Rio de Janeiro]] to develop production projects of the much needed equipment at this time of health crisis. At Universidade Federal Fluminense ([[Universidade Federal Fluminense|UFF]]), a group of professors and a master's student at the School of Engineering are already producing low-cost faceshield masks on [[3D printers]]. \n\nProfessor M\u00e1rcio Cataldi said that initially the production is being carried out on three printers in the homes of the members of the group, but next Monday (30) five more equipment will be used, and the eight will work in a laboratory of the School of Engineering. At the Federal University of Rio de Janeiro ([[UFRJ]]), the work is in partnership with the Pontifical Catholic University of Rio de Janeiro ([[PUC-Rio]]), the Federal University of the State of Rio de Janeiro [Unirio) and members of [[civil society]]. \n\nThe [[prototypes]] of facial protectors developed by UFRJ were validated by the Hospital Universit\u00e1rio Clementino Fraga Filho (HUCFF) and follow the guidelines of the National Health Surveillance Agency ([[Anvisa]]). At PUC-Rio, a group of researchers and professors from different institutions in the state is dedicated to production that can also extend to cloaks and valves, among other equipment used by doctors and nurses in the Unified Health System ([[Sistema \u00danico de Sa\u00fade|SUS]]) in the state. In addition to PUC-Rio and UFRJ, the group includes representatives from Unirio, Federation of Industries of the State of Rio de Janeiro ([[Firjan]]), National Service for Industrial Learning ([[Senai]]), [[state government]], National Institute of Technology (INT), Coppe [[UFRJ]], DASA Group, Clementino Fraga Filho University Hospital, Brazilian Navy and SOS 3D Covid 19. \n\nOne of the production sites is the Department of Arts and Design at PUC-Rio, with 16 printing units operating in the Volume and Prototyping. In addition to facial protectors manufactured in 3D printing and laser cutting, the university will produce [[N95 mask]]s, which are also already in short supply in health facilities. The PUC-Rio team includes professors Jo\u00e3o Victor de Melo and Gabriella Vaccari, and laboratories Diogo de Souza Marques and Hanna Claudia Marins.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/educacao/noticia/2020-03/universidades-e-sociedade-civil-se-juntam-para-produzir-mascaras|title=Universidades e sociedade civil se juntam para produzir m\u00e1scaras|date=26 March 2020|website=Ag\u00eancia Brasil}}</ref>\n\n===Preventive measures===\n\nOn 14 March, Approximately 40 military personnel from the Fire Department of the Federal District are scheduled and prepared to work in bus terminals and airports in the identification of people suspected of infection by Covid-19. The operation, which is expected to start in the next few days, will count on the help of state-of-the-art equipment capable of even detecting whether or not an environment has the presence of people who have already acquired the disease. The information was released on Saturday (14), at a press conference at the Buriti Palace, when officials of the corporation demonstrated part of the work they intend to develop to help fight the proliferation of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|author=Renata Moura, da Ag\u00eancia Bras\u00edlia |url=https://www.agenciabrasilia.df.gov.br/2020/03/14/corpo-de-bombeiros-vai-atuar-na-deteccao-de-casos-suspeitos/ |title=Corpo de Bombeiros vai atuar na detec\u00e7\u00e3o de casos suspeitos \u2013 Ag\u00eancia Bras\u00edlia |publisher=Agenciabrasilia.df.gov.br |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n[[File:COE (COVID-19) (49666502131).jpg|thumb|]]\n\nOn 16 March, Today (16) an Emergency Operations Center (COE) of the Municipal Health Secretariat (Sesau) was created to establish actions to combat and control Covid-19. The creation of the COE was based on the need to establish a response plan and a [[strategy]] for [[monitoring (medicine)|monitoring]] and supporting confirmed and suspected cases. The center will use urgent measures to prevent, control and contain risks, damages and [[public health]] problems.\n\nThe Emergency Operations Center will act jointly with other organs and sectors internal and external to Sesau and will be valid for six months, and may be extended for consecutive periods, if necessary, based on [[epidemiological]] indicators. Among the duties of COE-Covid-19 will be the analysis of patterns of occurrences, the distribution and confirmation of positive cases for the disease. The center will also develop flows and protocols, assistance and a laboratory for dealing with the virus in the public network. The COE should also train municipal employees and private entities, whether or not they are affiliated with the Unified Health System ([[Sistema \u00danico de Sa\u00fade|SUS]]), so that there is a standard in the measures taken to increase responses to the Public Health Emergency.<ref>{{cite web|author=CGNot\u00edcias Ag\u00eancia Municipal de Not\u00edcias de Campo Grande |url=http://www.campogrande.ms.gov.br/cgnoticias/noticias/prefeitura-cria-centro-de-operacoes-de-emergencias-coe-para-covid-19/ |title=Prefeitura cria Centro de Opera\u00e7\u00f5es de Emerg\u00eancias (COE) para Covid-19 &#124; CGNot\u00edcias |publisher=Campogrande.ms.gov.br |date=2020-03-16 |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Corpo de Bombeiros vai atuar na detec\u00e7\u00e3o de casos suspeitos - 49658924053.jpg|thumb|Brazilian firefighters will be helping in the detection of suspected cases]]\n\nOn 17 March, Brazilian authorities partially closed [[Brazil\u2013Venezuela border|their border]] with Venezuela. Health Minister Luiz Henrique Mandetta had urged closure of the border due to Venezuela's collapsing health system.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-venezuela-idUSKBN2143ZS|title=Brazil partially closing Venezuela border, allowing trucks|date=18 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318100317/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-venezuela-idUSKBN2143ZS|archive-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Rio de Janeiro and five other municipalities \u2014 [[S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo, Rio de Janeiro|S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo]], [[Guapimirim]], [[Niter\u00f3i]], [[Nova Igua\u00e7u]], and [[Mesquita, Rio de Janeiro|Mesquita]] \u2014 in the state of Rio de Janeiro have declared an [[State of emergency|emergency state]] to help contain the coronavirus. declared emergency situations in the area of public health.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/18/prefeitura-do-rio-declara-situacao-de-emergencia.ghtml|title=Rio e outros 5 munic\u00edpios do estado declaram situa\u00e7\u00e3o de emerg\u00eancia para conter o coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319214110/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/18/prefeitura-do-rio-declara-situacao-de-emergencia.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nThe following day, the government of Rio Grande do Sul declared a public calamity situation. Among the measures adopted are the prohibition of interstate travel and the restriction of items purchased in the markets.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rs/rio-grande-do-sul/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-decreta-situacao-de-calamidade-publica-no-rs-devido-ao-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RS decreta situa\u00e7\u00e3o de calamidade p\u00fablica devido ao coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175803/https://g1.globo.com/rs/rio-grande-do-sul/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-decreta-situacao-de-calamidade-publica-no-rs-devido-ao-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nOn 20 March, it was the government of Rio Grande do Norte that declared a public calamity situation.<ref name=\"auto12\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rn/rio-grande-do-norte/noticia/2020/03/20/governo-do-rn-decreta-calamidade-publica-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RN decreta calamidade p\u00fablica por causa do coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182944/https://g1.globo.com/rn/rio-grande-do-norte/noticia/2020/03/20/governo-do-rn-decreta-calamidade-publica-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Declara\u00e7\u00f5es \u00e0 Imprensa referentes ao Corona v\u00edrus em 18 de mar\u00e7o de 2020 - Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto 44.jpg|thumb|Government declarations about the disease on the [[Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto]] ]]\n\nOn 20 March, The Ministry of Health declared, on Friday (20), the recognition of community transmission of the coronavirus (Covid-19) throughout the national territory. This means that the whole of Brazil must unite against the virus. In practical terms, the declaration is a command from the Ministry of Health for all national managers to adopt measures to promote social distance and avoid agglomerations, known as non-pharmacological measures, that is, that do not involve the use of medicines or vaccines.<ref>{{cite web | last=Sa\u00fade | first=Minist\u00e9rio da | title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade declara transmiss\u00e3o comunit\u00e1ria nacional | website=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade | date=2020-03-20 | url=https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46568-ministerio-da-saude-declara-transmissao-comunitaria-nacional | language=pt | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nGovernment of Rio Grande do Norte decrees public calamity because of the coronavirus. The measure becomes effective on Friday (20), after being published in the Official Gazette of the State.<ref name=\"auto12\"/>\nIn remote voting, Senate approves state of public calamity because of coronavirus. On Friday (20), the Senate approved, in the first remote vote in the history of the House, the draft legislative decree that recognizes that the country is in a state of public calamity due to the global pandemic caused by the coronavirus. The vote was unanimous and 75 senators participated. The acting president of the Senate, Ant\u00f4nio Anastasia (PSD-MG), has already signed the promulgation of the text, which is already in force.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gazetadopovo.com.br/republica/breves/calamidade-publica-coronavirus-senado/|title=CONTE\u00daDO ABERTO: Em vota\u00e7\u00e3o remota, Senado aprova estado de calamidade p\u00fablica por causa de coronav\u00edrus|website=Gazeta do Povo|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321142802/https://www.gazetadopovo.com.br/republica/breves/calamidade-publica-coronavirus-senado/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, In SP, cases of coronavirus rise almost 40% in two hours. Deaths also increased in the period. Cities in the Campinas region declared an emergency situation due to the pandemic of the new coronavirus. In addition to the metropolis, Hortol\u00e2ndia, Holambra, Indaiatuba, Itapira, Jaguari\u00fana, Mogi Gua\u00e7u, Mogi Mirim, Paul\u00ednia, Sumar\u00e9 and \u00c1guas de Lindoia issued decrees with special measures to contain the progress of Covid-19 cases. Valinhos and Vinhedo determined a state of public calamity. Americana is in a state of attention.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariodolitoral.com.br/saude/em-sp-casos-de-coronavirus-sobem-quase-40-em-duas-horas/133224/|title=Em SP, casos de coronav\u00edrus sobem quase 40% em duas horas|website=diariodolitoral.com.br|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321170926/https://www.diariodolitoral.com.br/saude/em-sp-casos-de-coronavirus-sobem-quase-40-em-duas-horas/133224/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/campinas-regiao/noticia/2020/03/21/coronavirus-veja-lista-de-cidades-em-estado-de-emergencia-ou-calamidade-publica-e-o-que-muda-com-decretos-na-regiao-de-campinas.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: veja lista de cidades em estado de emerg\u00eancia ou calamidade p\u00fablica e o que muda com decretos na regi\u00e3o de Campinas|website=G1|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163920/https://g1.globo.com/sp/campinas-regiao/noticia/2020/03/21/coronavirus-veja-lista-de-cidades-em-estado-de-emergencia-ou-calamidade-publica-e-o-que-muda-com-decretos-na-regiao-de-campinas.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn view of the advance of the Covid-19 outbreak, the federal government closed land borders with Argentina, Bolivia, Colombia, French Guiana, Guyana, Paraguay, Peru and Suriname. The border with Venezuela is already closed. The ordinance was signed by Sergio Moro, Minister of Justice, Luiz Henrique Mandetta, of Health, and Braga Netto, of the Civil House. There is an expectation that air travel will also be stopped soon. Rio de Janeiro declared an emergency situation and determined, among other measures, the suspension, as of Saturday, 21, of the air bridge between Rio de Janeiro and S\u00e3o Paulo. The governor of S\u00e3o Paulo, Jo\u00e3o Doria (PSDB), recommended closing the shopping centers and gyms in the metropolitan region. In addition, classes in public and private schools are also being suspended.<ref name=\"exame\"/>\n\nOn 24 March, The six cemeteries in the Federal District, managed by Campo da Esperan\u00e7a Servi\u00e7os Ltda., Have adopted specific protocols to avoid crowding people and prevent further cases of transmission of the new coronavirus. One of the measures foresees that patients who die as a result of the disease caused by the microorganism, Covid-19, will not be able to have a funeral ceremony at the DF units, only the burial, in compliance with a protocol defined by local Executive bodies.\nThe company released a letter that, among other measures, establishes that the other funerals cannot last more than two hours - in addition to the 30 minutes foreseen for the procession - and that the chapels cannot have more than 10 people at the same time. The inspection and control of this care is up to the families themselves. The measures, adopted since Tuesday (3/17) were approved by the Secretariat of Justice and Citizenship (Sejus).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/app/noticia/cidades/2020/03/24/interna_cidadesdf,836378/cemiterios-do-df-nao-poderao-fazer-velorio-de-vitimas-da-covid-19.shtml |title=Cemit\u0436rios do DF n\u0441o poder\u0441o fazer vel\u0437rio de v\u044ctimas da Covid-19 - Cidades |publisher=Correiobraziliense.com.br |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Prefeitura de Petr\u00f3polis - Sirenes m\u00f3veis s\u00e3o usadas para alertar popula\u00e7\u00e3o sobre perigo do Coronav\u00edrus.webm|thumb|Sirens used to warn people about the dangers of the pandemic]]\n\nOn 25 March, The city continues to advise residents to stay in their homes. This Wednesday (25.03), the mobile sirens of the Secretariat of [[Civil Defense]] and Voluntary Actions were in the Community of [[Complexo do Alem\u00e3o|Alem\u00e3o]] and Neylor, At\u00edlio Marotti, Vale do Carangola and Bairro da [[Gl\u00f3ria]]. The action reinforces the prevention work carried out by the municipal government, with the objective of preventing the proliferation of the coronavirus (Covid-19).\nIn addition to the four mobile sirens, the 20 sets of the Alert and Alarm System installed in 12 [[communities]] in [[Petr\u00f3polis]] also emit guidance messages. The equipment plays in the neighborhoods daily at 10, 16 and 20h.\n\nThe locations with fixed sirens are: Gentio, Buraco do Sapo, 24 de Maio, Alto da Serra, {{ill|Bingen |pt|lt=Bingen}}, Dr. Thouzet, {{ill|Independ\u00eancia |pt|lt=Independ\u00eancia}}, Quitandinha, S\u00e3o Sebasti\u00e3o, S\u00e3o Paulo|S\u00e3o Sebasti\u00e3o, Sergeant Boening, Sim\u00e9ria and Vila Felipe. All equipment is functioning normally.\nThe operation with mobile sirens began last weekend and has already passed through Araras, Secretary, [[Posse, Goi\u00e1s|Posse]], {{ill|Centro |pt|lt=Centro}}, Cascatinha, Itamarati, Corr\u00eaas, {{ill|Nogueira |pt|lt=Nogueira}}, Alto da Serra and [[S\u00e3o Sebasti\u00e3o, S\u00e3o Paulo|S\u00e3o Sebasti\u00e3o]]. Other locations will be served in the coming days. The call is for people to stay at home.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.petropolis.rj.gov.br/pmp/index.php/imprensa/noticias/item/15664-sirenes-m%C3%B3veis-s%C3%A3o-usadas-no-retiro-carangola-e-corr%C3%AAas |title=Sirenes m\u00f3veis s\u00e3o usadas no Retiro, Carangola e Corr\u00eaas |publisher=Petropolis.rj.gov.br |date=2020-01-04 |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, The health minister, Henrique Mandetta, changed this Saturday the tone again of his declarations on social isolation. On Wednesday, he had adjusted his speech to that of President [[Jair Bolsonaro]], opposed to a more general isolation and favorable to the isolation only of chronic patients and the elderly and people aged 60 and over. Although it was not direct and explicit, on Saturday Mandetta was more emphatic in advocating that people who can stay at home. He justified his defense that people should stay at home so that the health system is not overburdened, increasing the lethality of Covid 19 due to lack of beds and ICU.<ref name=\"globo1\"/>\n\n===Foreign policy===\nOn 19 March, [[Eduardo Bolsonaro]], son of President Jair Bolsonaro, set off a diplomatic dispute with China, Brazil's largest trading partner, when he retweeted a message blaming the [[Communist Party of China|Chinese Communist Party]] for the virus.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/rio-reports-first-coronavirus-deaths-163812406.html Brazil coronavirus cases top 600, diplomatic spat with China bubbles] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320192215/https://news.yahoo.com/rio-reports-first-coronavirus-deaths-163812406.html |date=20 March 2020 }} By Pedro Fonseca, Reuters, 19 March 2020</ref> Yang Wanming, China's top diplomat in Brazil, later retweeted a message saying \"The Bolsonaro family is the great poison of this country.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Bolsonaro's son enrages Beijing by blaming China for coronavirus crisis |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/coronavirus-bolsonaro-son-china-row |work=The Guardian |date=19 March 2020 |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320190353/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/coronavirus-bolsonaro-son-china-row |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\nBolsonaro made a televised speech about the pandemic, during which both pro and anti-Bolsonaro ''[[Cacerolazo|panela\u00e7os]]'' broke out in the largest cities of Brazil.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51955679|title=Brazil coronavirus protesters urge 'Bolsonaro out'|date=19 March 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322135850/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51955679|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \nAccording to one poll, 64% of Brazilians reject the way Bolsonaro has been handling the pandemic, while 44.8% support his [[impeachment]], an all-time high.<ref>[https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-19/gestao-de-bolsonaro-do-coronavirus-e-reprovada-por-64-e-45-se-dizem-a-favor-de-impeachment.html \"Gest\u00e3o de Bolsonaro do coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 reprovada por 64%, e 45% se dizem a favor de impeachment\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323021820/https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-19/gestao-de-bolsonaro-do-coronavirus-e-reprovada-por-64-e-45-se-dizem-a-favor-de-impeachment.html |date=23 March 2020 }}. ''El Pa\u00eds''. 19 March 2020.</ref> \nAccording to some sources in the Congress, Bolsonaro is shutting down political dialogue on purpose. They claim he is forcing his impeachment as a way to mobilize his supporters.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/colunas/tales-faria/2020/03/21/para-o-congresso-bolsonaro-quer-que-tentem-impeachment-para-ter-confronto.htm|title=Para o Congresso, Bolsonaro quer que tentem impeachment para ter confronto|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321172504/https://noticias.uol.com.br/colunas/tales-faria/2020/03/21/para-o-congresso-bolsonaro-quer-que-tentem-impeachment-para-ter-confronto.htm|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Banners offend China's politician at the embassy, which he calls an act of \"clowning\". Videos of offenses against Chinese politicians began to circulate on social networks. In one of them, made from a car, a white man in a yellow shirt, a dark hat and cream pants films two tracks with bad words in Portuguese and English. In them, the target is the [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|General Secretary]] ([[paramount leader]]) of [[Communist Party of China|Chinese Communist Party]], [[Xi Jinping]]. One calls the coronavirus \"China virus\" or virus from China. Another uses a curse word that far-right militants began to spread after one of President Jair Bolsonaro's sons, Rio de Janeiro councilor Carlos Bolsonaro (PSC), complained about a report in Veja magazine. The president of the Brazil-China Parliamentary Front, deputy Fausto Pinato, demanded that President Jair Bolsonaro deny his son, under pain of assuming that he was agreeing with him. The presidents of the Chamber and the Senate, Rodrigo Maia (DEM-RJ) and Davi Alcolumbre (DEM-AP), apologized to the Chinese. Yesterday, Jair Bolsonaro said he would not apologize. However, he said that the subject was \"page turned\" and that the country's relationship with the Chinese was \"very good\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/21/faixas-embaixada-china-brasilia-xingamento-presidente-xi-jinping.htm|title=Faixas ofendem pol\u00edtico da China em embaixada, que chama ato de \"palha\u00e7ada\"|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321154652/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/21/faixas-embaixada-china-brasilia-xingamento-presidente-xi-jinping.htm|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 01 April, president [[Jair Bolsonaro]] also said that he spoke today, by phone, with the [[President of the United States]], Donald Tump about \"this problem that is worldwide\". \"Obviously, we are together in the search for the best for our countries,\" he said in the statement to the press. Earlier, in a publication on [[Twitter]], Bolsonaro reported that he exchanged information about the impact of [[covid-19]] and about the experiences in the use of [[hydroxychloroquine]]. \"On occasion, we reaffirm the mutual solidarity between the two countries,\" he wrote. [[Chloroquine]], and its [[hydroxychloroquine]] variation, is being tested for the treatment of hospitalized patients with covid-19. These [[drugs]] are usually used against [[malaria]] in cases of [[lupus]] and [[rheumatoid]] [[arthritis]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Jair M. Bolsonaro (Verified account) |url=https://twitter.com/jairbolsonaro/status/1245358462953050115 |title=Jair M. Bolsonaro on Twitter: \"- Nesta manh\u00e3 tive contato telef\u00f4nico com o Presidente dos EUA, @realDonaldTrump.Trocamos informa\u00e7\u00f5es sobre o impacto do covid-19, bem como experi\u00eancias no uso da hidroxicloroquina. - Na oportunidade, reafirmamos a solidariedade m\u00fatua entre os dois pa\u00edses. Com @ernestofaraujo\" |publisher=Twitter.com |date=2010-03-31 |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/politica/noticia/2020-04/governo-anuncia-r-200-bilhoes-para-socorrer-trabalhadores-e-empresas|title=Governo anuncia R$ 200 bilh\u00f5es para socorrer trabalhadores e empresas|date=1 April 2020|website=Ag\u00eancia Brasil}}</ref>\n\n===Internal policy===\nPresident [[Jair Bolsonaro]] has been criticized for his handling of the coronavirus crisis.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/03/coronavirus-bolsonaro-brazil-panelaco.html|title=Could the Coronavirus Topple Jair Bolsonaro?|last=Dias|first=Isabela|date=20 March 2020|website=Slate|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322031616/https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/03/coronavirus-bolsonaro-brazil-panelaco.html|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 March, he referred to the pandemic as a \"fantasy\" created by the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/10/bolsonaro-diz-que-questao-do-coronavirus-e-muito-mais-fantasia.ghtml|title=Bolsonaro diz que 'pequena crise' do coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 'mais fantasia' e n\u00e3o 'isso tudo' que m\u00eddia propaga|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322031617/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/10/bolsonaro-diz-que-questao-do-coronavirus-e-muito-mais-fantasia.ghtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Bolsonaro, who was being monitored by doctors after his Press Secretary tested positive for COVID-19, was heavily criticized for meeting his supporters in a public parade in Bras\u00edlia without wearing a mask.<ref name=\"auto11\"/> Later, impeachment cases were brought up against the President for his participation in the parade, which some viewed as anti-democratic, and also for posing a threat to public health.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/intervozes/coronavirus-desmascara-a-politica-de-morte-de-bolsonaro/|title=Coronav\u00edrus desmascara a pol\u00edtica de morte de Bolsonaro|date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321194634/https://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/intervozes/coronavirus-desmascara-a-politica-de-morte-de-bolsonaro/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, President Jair Bolsonaro said on Wednesday that the spread of the new coronavirus (Covid-19) in Brazil worries the government, but called on the population to commit themselves to following the guidelines of the authorities and avoiding the climate of panic in the country. \"We will have difficult days, hard days ahead. Now, it will be less difficult if each of you worries about yourself, your relatives and your friends. Only in this way, following the precepts dictated by the Ministry of Health, as, in the first place, instead, basic hygiene measures, we can lengthen the infection curve, and so that we, the Executive Branch, through our means, hospitals and other health agencies, serve those in need, and serve with quality \", says the president.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ovale.com.br/_conteudo/brasil/2020/03/99637-bolsonaro-diz-que-nao-ha-motivo-para-panico-e-anuncia--voucher.html|title=Bolsonaro diz que n\u00e3o h\u00e1 motivo para p\u00e2nico e anuncia 'voucher'|website=www.ovale.com.br}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, Bolsonaro criticized the governor of Rio de Janeiro, Wilson Witzel (PSC), for asking for the suspension of the arrival of flights from states where contamination by the new coronavirus is confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/bolsonaro-critica-witzel-por-fechar-aeroporto-parece-que-rj-e-outro-pais.htm|title=Bolsonaro critica Witzel por querer impedir voos para o Rio de Janeiro|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195055/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/bolsonaro-critica-witzel-por-fechar-aeroporto-parece-que-rj-e-outro-pais.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nBolsonaro says that closing shopping malls and commerce hurts the economy. In the midst of the COVID-19 pandemic, experts from around the world have suggested measures to restrict the circulation of individuals as one of the most efficient ways to contain the spread of the virus. However, then-president Jair Bolsonaro said on Friday (20) that he was against the closing of trade decreed by most state governors as a measure to combat the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bnews.com.br/noticias/economia/coronavirus/262603,bolsonaro-diz-que-fechar-shoppings-e-comercio-prejudica-a-economia.html|title=Bolsonaro diz que fechar shoppings e com\u00e9rcio prejudica a economia|website=BNews|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195057/https://www.bnews.com.br/noticias/economia/coronavirus/262603,bolsonaro-diz-que-fechar-shoppings-e-comercio-prejudica-a-economia.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nDoria counters Bolsonaro: \"we are doing what he does not do, lead\". The governor of S\u00e3o Paulo, Jo\u00e3o Doria Jr (PSDB), countered today a statement by president Jair Bolsonaro and said that the governors are playing the role that would be his, which is to lead in a pandemic moment for the new coronavirus. Earlier in Bras\u00edlia, Bolsonaro criticized what he called extreme measures, such as \"closing shopping malls and fairs\". He did not specifically mention Doria, but the governor of S\u00e3o Paulo defended the stance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/doria-rebate-bolsonaro-estamos-fazendo-o-que-ele-nao-faz-liderar.htm|title=Doria rebate Bolsonaro: 'estamos fazendo o que ele n\u00e3o faz, liderar'|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175802/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/doria-rebate-bolsonaro-estamos-fazendo-o-que-ele-nao-faz-liderar.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nBrazil is the 2nd country with more cases of coronavirus at the top of the government. Just behind Iran and followed by France, the Brazilian government has at least thirteen prominent politicians contaminated. The confirmation on Thursday 18 that the Minister of Mines and Energy, Bento Albuquerque, and the President of the Senate, Davi Alcolumbre, contracted the new coronavirus makes Brazil the second country with more cases of the disease at the top of the government. With 13 confirmed, it is second only to Iran, which has 24 sick officials.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veja.abril.com.br/mundo/brasil-e-2o-pais-com-mais-casos-de-coronavirus-na-alta-cupula-do-governo/|title=Brasil \u00e9 2\u00ba pa\u00eds com mais casos de coronav\u00edrus na alta c\u00fapula do governo|website=VEJA|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320132618/https://veja.abril.com.br/mundo/brasil-e-2o-pais-com-mais-casos-de-coronavirus-na-alta-cupula-do-governo/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, For Congress, Bolsonaro wants them to try impeachment to have a confrontation. The presidents of the Chamber, Rodrigo Maia (DEM-RJ), and the Senate, Davi Alcolumbre (DEM-AP), as well as the leaders of the main parties of the Congress no longer believe in the possibility of productive dialogue with President Jair Bolsonaro.<ref name=\"auto9\"/>\nCoronavirus unmasks Bolsonaro's death policy. How the scrapping of SUS and public communication make Brazil more susceptible to the pandemic. After Jair Bolsonaro participated in last Sunday's acts against the Supreme Federal Court and the National Congress, a district deputy and a group of three PSOL parliamentarians and militants filed two impeachment cases against the President of the Republic for supporting anti-democratic demonstrations. A portion of civil society bet on the annulment of the ticket that elected him, in view of the cases of disinformation committed still in the electoral process. The coronavirus pandemic spells out another series of riots that Bolsonaro has been committing in the exercise of the Presidency of the Republic.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> On 23 March, Rodrigo Maia stated that Brazil might need between $78.1&nbsp;billion to combat coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-budget-idUSKBN21A3GJ|title=Brazil needs up to $78&nbsp;billion to fight coronavirus crisis \u2013 Congress leader|date=23 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095115/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-budget-idUSKBN21A3GJ|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, on CNN Brasil, Bolsonaro criticized the quarantine decree and called Doria a lunatic. The president gave an exclusive interview to the broadcaster and spoke about the measures to contain the new coronavirus, the confidence in the hydroxychloroquine medicine and also harshly criticized the state governors. In the interview, Bolsonaro considered that the governors who decreed quarantine in their states are extrapolating. They are giving an \"overdose of the medicine and that the excess medicine becomes a poison\". Jo\u00e3o Doria, governor of S\u00e3o Paulo, and Wilson Witzel, governor of Rio de Janeiro, were criticized by the president. \"Doria is a lunatic. He denies that he used my name to be elected governor and is taking advantage to grow politically,\" said Bolsonaro. \"The subject (of the discussions) has to be focused only on the problem that lies ahead, which is the coronavirus.\" The president also commented on the suspicion that he was infected with the new coronavirus and justified the use of the term \"little flu\" to refer to COVID-19. \"Several times the press wanted me to do the third test. I said that they were very concerned about my health and, after having been stabbed before, I am calm with this virus. I said it would be a 'little flu' for me.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/politica/2020-03-22/na-cnn-brasil-bolsonaro-critica-decreto-de-quarentena-e-chama-doria-de-lunatico.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324101225/https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/politica/2020-03-22/na-cnn-brasil-bolsonaro-critica-decreto-de-quarentena-e-chama-doria-de-lunatico.html |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, president Jair Bolsonaro said on Monday that it is not yet time to talk about postponing municipal elections this year because of the outbreak of the new coronavirus. \"I am not in the business of postponing municipal elections, it is still too early,\" he said, as he left the Pal\u00e1cio da Alvorada. \"They ask if Mandetta's popularity is higher than mine. So much!\", the president said. Bolsonaro also stated that panic cannot be spread to society: \"We cannot bring panic to society, because panic is also a more serious disease.\" The president pointed out that today he will have a meeting, by videoconference with governors from the North and Northeast regions. And he will hear proposals to combat the new coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/politica/2020-03-23/bolsonaro-e-cedo-para-falar-em-adiamento-das-eleicoes-por-causa-do-coronavirus.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324101223/https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/politica/2020-03-23/bolsonaro-e-cedo-para-falar-em-adiamento-das-eleicoes-por-causa-do-coronavirus.html |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Pronunciamento do presidente da Rep\u00fablica Jair Bolsonaro em 24-03-2020.webm|thumb|President Jair Bolsonaro's official announcement on 24th March.]]\n\nOn 24 March, president [[Jair Bolsonaro]] declared that the routine in the country must return to reality and that the Brazilian press spread the panic around the coronavirus, which he called again \"little flu\". Speaking on radio and television, Bolsonaro also criticized governors for determining quarantine \u2013 with trade and border closures \u2013 and questioned why schools were closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/24/covid-19-bolsonaro-culpa-imprensa-por-panico-e-volta-a-falar-gripezinha.htm|title=Bolsonaro critica imprensa e fechamento de escolas e diz que crise passar\u00e1|website=noticias.uol.com.br|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/regiao-dos-lagos/noticia/2020/03/25/autoridades-no-rj-reagem-a-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-que-critica-confinamento-em-massa.ghtml|title=Autoridades no RJ reagem a pronunciamento de Bolsonaro que pede fim do 'confinamento em massa'|website=G1|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref> \nPoliticians and authorities reacted to President Jair Bolsonaro's pronouncement about the coronavirus pandemic on Tuesday night (24). The president called for \"a return to normal\", an end to \"mass confinement\" and said that the media had spread \"dread\". Senate President Davi Alcolumbre (DEM-AP) released a note in which he classified Bolsonaro's speech as \"serious\" and said the country needs \"serious leadership\". The president of the Chamber of Deputies, Rodrigo Maia (DEM-RJ), affirmed that the statement \"was wrong when attacking the press, the governors and specialists in public health\".\nA large number of the Brazilian politicians spoke out against this statement by the President of the Republic{{efn|They include: [[Davi Alcolumbre]] (DEM-AP) President of the Senate, [[Rodrigo Maia]] (DEM-RJ) President of the Chamber, [[Felipe Santa Cruz]] President of the OAB, [[Gilmar Mendes]] Minister of the STF, [[Wilson Witzel]] (PSC) governor of Rio de Janeiro, [[Helder Barbalho]] (MDB) governor of Par\u00e1, [[Alexandre Frota]] (PSDB-SP) federal deputy, [[Joice Hasselmann]] (PSL-SP) federal deputy, [[Janaina Paschoal]] (PSL-SP) state deputy, [[Rodrigo Pacheco (politician)|Rodrigo Pacheco]] (DEM-MG) senator, [[Kim Kataguiri]] (DEM-SP) federal deputy, [[Jos\u00e9 Serra]] (PSDB) former Minister of Health, Jos\u00e9 Ricardo Roriz vice president of Fiesp, [[Leila Barros|Leila do V\u00f4lei]] (PSB-DF) senator, [[Renato Casagrande]] (PSB) governor of Esp\u00edrito Santo, [[Wellington Dias]] (PT), governor of Piau\u00ed, [[F\u00e1tima Bezerra]] (PT) governor of Rio Grande do Norte, [[Antonio Anastasia]] (PSD-MG) senator, [[Fernando Henrique Cardoso]] former president, [[Jo\u00e3o Amo\u00eado]] ex-president of the New Party, [[Enio Verri]] (PT-PR) federal deputy, [[Eduardo Braga]] (MDB-AM) senator, [[Humberto Costa]] (PT-PE) senator, [[Randolfe Rodrigues]] (Rede-AP) senator, [[Alessandro Molon]] (PSB-RJ) federal deputy, [[Fl\u00e1vio Dino]] (PCdoB) governor of Maranh\u00e3o, [[Jos\u00e9 Nobre Guimar\u00e3es]] (PT-CE) federal deputy, [[Rog\u00e9rio Carvalho Santos|Rog\u00e9rio Carvalho]] (PT-SE) senator, [[Fernanda Melchionna]] (PSOL-RS) federal deputy, [[Weverton Rocha]] (PDT-MA) senator, [[Marcelo Freixo]] (PSOL-RJ) federal deputy, [[Paulo Pimenta (politician)|Paulo Pimenta]] (PT -RS) federal deputy, [[Jean-Paul Prates]] (PT-RN) senator, [[Eliziane Gama]] (Cidadania-MA) senator, [[Marcelo Ramos Rodrigues|Marcelo Ramos]] (PL-AM) federal deputy, [[Arnaldo Jardim]] (Cidadania-SP) federal deputy, [[Reinaldo Azambuja]] (PSDB) governor of Mato Grosso do Sul, [[Wilson Lima]] (PSC) governor of Amazonas.<ref name=\"24globo\" />}} The [[PSDB]], the Brazilian Press Association (ABI), the Secretaries of Health of the Northeast, the Brazilian Society of Infectology, also spoke against the president's speech. In favor of the president's speech, his two sons [[Eduardo Bolsonaro]] (no party) federal deputy and [[Fl\u00e1vio Bolsonaro]] (no party) senator, along with Vitor Hugo (PSL-GO), federal deputy, spoke.<ref name=24globo>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/veja-repercussao-ao-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-em-que-ele-pediu-volta-a-normalidade-fim-do-confinamento-e-disse-que-meios-de-comunicacao-espalharam-pavor.ghtml |title=Archived copy |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325024638/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/veja-repercussao-ao-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-em-que-ele-pediu-volta-a-normalidade-fim-do-confinamento-e-disse-que-meios-de-comunicacao-espalharam-pavor.ghtml |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\nBrazilian cities register pots against Bolsonaro for the eighth consecutive day. [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Rio de Janeiro, [[Bras\u00edlia]], [[Belo Horizonte]] and [[Recife]] were some of the cities in which people threw pots during the president's speech last Tuesday (24). Brasilienses protested, against the pronouncement of the President of the Republic, Jair Bolsonaro (without party). \"Pots\" were recorded in \u00c1guas Claras, in the Southwest, in Cruzeiro, in Asa Norte, in Asa Sul and in Taguatinga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/cidades-brasileiras-registram-panelacos-contra-bolsonaro.ghtml |title=Cidades brasileiras registram panela\u0102\u00a7os contra Bolsonaro pelo oitavo dia seguido &#124; Pol\u0102\u00adtica &#124; G1 |publisher=G1.globo.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metropoles.com/distrito-federal/df-tem-panelaco-contra-bolsonaro-durante-pronunciamento-na-tv|title=DF tem panela\u00e7o contra Bolsonaro durante pronunciamento na TV|date=24 March 2020|website=Metr\u00f3poles}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, The governor of [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Jo\u00e3o Doria]] (PSDB), received death threats on his cell phone and on social media the day after he attended a meeting of governors and repudiated the statement by President [[Jair Bolsonaro]] (sem partido), made on national network, about the measures adopted by governors to fight the coronavirus. In addition to the death threats, the messages spoke of breaking into Doria's home, where the governor lives with his family. Doria registered a police report on Thursday night (26) and the Civil Police will investigate the threats. The governor's house, located in Jardins, a prime area of S\u00e3o Paulo, was surrounded and protected by the Military Police (PM). According to the government, there are indications that the attacks were allegedly articulated by the \"hate office\", led by the president's son, [[Carlos Bolsonaro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/27/doria-recebe-ameacas-de-morte.ghtml|title=Doria recebe amea\u00e7as de morte ap\u00f3s trocar acusa\u00e7\u00f5es com Bolsonaro|website=G1}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\n===Economy===\nEconomists expect an [[economic stagnation]] for the country in 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://diariodocomercio.com.br/exclusivo/economia-brasileira-sofrera-forte-impacto-com-o-novo-coronavirus/|title=Economia brasileira sofrer\u00e1 forte impacto com o novo coronav\u00edrus|first=Mara|last=Bianchetti|date=21 March 2020|website=Di\u00e1rio do Com\u00e9rcio|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322062357/https://diariodocomercio.com.br/exclusivo/economia-brasileira-sofrera-forte-impacto-com-o-novo-coronavirus/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> As such, on 16 March, the [[Ministry of Economy (Brazil)|Ministry of Economy]] announced a stimulus package of R$147.3&nbsp;billion (US$29&nbsp;billion) to help the economy against the effects of the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.poder360.com.br/economia/guedes-anuncia-pacote-de-r-147-bilhoes-para-combater-pandemia-de-covid-19/|title=Guedes anuncia pacote de R$147 bilh\u00f5es para combater pandemia de covid-19|website=Poder 360|date=16 March 2020}}</ref> The Brazilian government is also in negotiations with the [[New Development Bank]] to receive an aid package for its COVID-19 efforts; China received one billion USD from the same institution.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/banco-de-desenvolvimento-do-brics-libera-ajuda-de-r-5-bilhoes-a-china,9bc26d72a411019e55adb6bdd0a3094asut8ttyw.html|title=Banco de Desenvolvimento do BRICS libera ajuda de R$5 bilh\u00f5es \u00e0 China|website=Terra|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321195758/https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/banco-de-desenvolvimento-do-brics-libera-ajuda-de-r-5-bilhoes-a-china,9bc26d72a411019e55adb6bdd0a3094asut8ttyw.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Economy Minister [[Paulo Guedes]] announced a series of aid measures to reduce the impact on the economy that will be caused by Covid-19. A scholarship for self-employed professionals, in the amount of R $200, is being prepared, in addition to the payment guarantee for workers who have reduced working hours.<ref name=\"exame\"/>\n\nOn 22 March, Crisis of the new coronavirus poses challenges for the [[industry]] and for [[Brazil]]. Now, the outlook is that the country's growth this year will be negative, culminating in an unprecedented economic [[recession]]. In this new scenario, the industrial sector, the largest job generator in the country, will be the most affected. The crisis generated by the new coronavirus abruptly interrupted the recovery cycle in [[industrial activity]] in [[Brazil]]. The government has announced measures in recent days to prevent the economic slowdown, but some sectors are already being impacted. A survey carried out by the Brazilian Association of the [[Electrical]] and Electronic Industry (Abinee) at the beginning of March showed that 70% of the associated companies already have problems with the supply of components, which are mainly produced in [[China]] and other [[Asian]] countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://noticias.portaldaindustria.com.br/noticias/economia/crise-do-novo-coronavirus-promove-desafios-para-a-industria-e-para-o-brasil/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095459/https://noticias.portaldaindustria.com.br/noticias/economia/crise-do-novo-coronavirus-promove-desafios-para-a-industria-e-para-o-brasil/ |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, government announces package of R$ 85.8 billion for states and municipalities. Amount involves transfers to the health area, recomposition of transfers of constitutional funds and suspension of the maturity of debts of the states with the Union.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/2020/03/23/coronavirus-governo-anuncia-pacote-de-r-858-bilhoes-para-estados-e-municipios.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: governo anuncia pacote de R$ 85,8 bilh\u00f5es para estados e munic\u00edpios|website=G1}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, The government last week announced a monthly aid of R$ 200 for informal, microentrepreneurs or unemployed professionals for the duration of the coronavirus crisis. According to the [[Ministry of Economy]], this measure - which has not yet been made official - should benefit between 15 and 20 million people and seeks to guarantee income for those workers who have no fixed income and, in general, also do not contribute to [[social security]]. The expectation is that R$ 15 billion will be injected into the economy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/2020/03/24/quem-deve-ter-direito-e-como-deve-funcionar-o-auxilio-de-r-200-para-trabalhadores-informais.ghtml|title=Quem deve ter direito e como deve funcionar o aux\u00edlio de R$ 200 para trabalhadores informais|website=G1}}</ref>\nThe House of Representatives approved on Thursday night (26), a bill that guarantees emergency income for self-employed [[workers]], [[informal]] and [[without]] fixed income during the crisis caused by the coronavirus pandemic. The proposal now goes to the Senate. The project provides resources of R$ 600 for Brazilians in situations of social [[vulnerability]], but in practice, it can reach R$ 1,200 per family. The government had initially proposed R$ 200 per person. With the defeat previously sanctioned, the government authorized its leaders to negotiate the approved amount.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.redebrasilatual.com.br/politica/2020/03/camara-coronavirus-renda-emergencial/|title=C\u00e2mara aprova renda emergencial e derrota proposta 'aviltante' do governo|date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, the [[federal government]] today announced the creation of a credit line for the payment of salaries for employees of small and medium-sized companies for up to two months. On the other hand, the entrepreneur will have to commit himself not to lay off workers due to the crisis caused by the coronavirus pandemic. In total, the volume of [[investment]] may reach R$ 40 billion (R$ 20 billion per month) and serve around 1.4 million [[companies]] and 12.2 million [[workers]]. Most of the money (85%) will be injected by the [[federal government]] and 15% by private banks. In practice, this means that the government will have 85% of the default risk and the banks with the remaining 15%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economia.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2020/03/27/governo-cria-linha-de-credito-para-bancar-folha-de-pequena-e-media-empresas.htm|title=Governo anuncia R$ 40 bi para empresas pequenas e m\u00e9dias pagarem sal\u00e1rios|website=economia.uol.com.br}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the secretary of the [[National Treasury]], Mansueto Almeida, said this Saturday (28) that the government will \"believe\" in the registration of people who present themselves as informal workers to receive the payment of the benefit of R$ 600 as a form of assistance in the face of the pandemic of the coronavirus. According to him, if someone receives the amount wrongly, it will be resolved later. He also said that the primary deficit in public accounts (expenses greater than revenues, not counting interest on public debt) will overcome the barrier of R$ 300 billion this year due to spending to combat the coronavirus pandemic and reduce the effects of the crisis on the economy and unemployment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/2020/03/28/tesouro-indica-flexibilidade-para-pagar-auxilio-aos-informais-e-diz-que-rombo-fiscal-vai-superar-r-300-bi-em-2020.ghtml|title=Governo aceitar\u00e1 autodeclara\u00e7\u00e3o de quem n\u00e3o tem renda e prev\u00ea d\u00e9ficit de R$ 300 bilh\u00f5es em 2020|website=G1}}</ref>\n\n[[File:TV BrasilGov - Coletiva de imprensa do presidente Jair Bolsonaro em 01-04-2020.webm|thumb|TV BrasilGov - Coletiva de imprensa. O Presidente Jair Bolsonaro faz pronunciamento no dia 01/04/2020.]]\n\nOn 01 April, President [[Jair Bolsonaro]] announced today (1st) about R $ 200 billion in measures to help [[workers]] and [[companies]] and help [[states]] and [[municipalities]] in facing the effects of the crisis caused by the pandemic of the new coronavirus. Speaking to the press at the [[Planalto Palace]], Bolsonaro explained that, from today to tomorrow, three provisional measures (MPs) will be issued and the project that [[provides]] for R $ 600 emergency aid for [[informal]], self-employed and without fixed income workers will be sanctioned.\n\nAlongside the president, Economy Minister [[Paulo Guedes]] explained that this aid will cost R$ 98 billion to public coffers and should [[benefit]] 54 million Brazilians. \u201cSo that they have the resources in the next three months to face the first wave of impact, which is the health wave. There is another wave coming from economic dislocation that threatens us \u201d, he said.\nThe [[federal government]] will also transfer R$ 16 billion to [[state]] and [[municipal]] participation funds. \"It is to reinforce this fight on the front, where the virus is attacking, the [[health]] and [[safety]] systems\", explained Guedes.\n\n===Education===\nOn 20 March, The pandemic has [[impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education|impacted education all over the world]]. In over a hundred countries, there were nationwide school closures. However, President Jair Bolsonaro has issued few country-wide measures to slow the spread of the virus,<ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200316-as-latin-america-takes-steps-to-counter-coronavirus-brazil-s-bolsonaro-snubs-warnings|title=Latin America takes steps to counter coronavirus, Brazil's Bolsonaro snubs warnings|date=16 March 2020|publisher=France 24|access-date=16 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320165406/https://www.france24.com/en/20200316-as-latin-america-takes-steps-to-counter-coronavirus-brazil-s-bolsonaro-snubs-warnings|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-panama-idUSKBN20Y3FA|title=Latin American countries order school closures over coronavirus fears|date=12 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=16 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320165410/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-panama-idUSKBN20Y3FA|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \nand because the federal government failed to act appropriately regarding the pandemic and had, as of 20 March, not decided to cancel classes in the whole country, lower instances of government had to act autonomously. As such, municipal, state, and private schools and universities had different reactions regarding the suspension of classes. Classes were suspended at once, gradually or not at all. Some of them were replaced with [[distance education]] or simply postponed. Because of that, there are only \"localized\" (as opposed to \"national\") school closures, according to [[UNESCO]].<ref name=\"UNESCO\">{{cite web|url=https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures|title=COVID-19 Educational Disruption and Response|publisher=UNESCO|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321000612/https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Favelas===\n\n[[File:TVFolha - Como a pandemia afeta uma favela.webm|thumb|TVFolha - Como a pandemia afeta uma favela]]\n\nOn 16 March, [[Rocinha]] residents' association, south of [[Rio de Janeiro]], recommends that [[tourists]] do not visit a [[community]] with the intention of preventing the spread of new coronaviruses. In a video published on social networks, the president of the region, Wallace Pereira, said that he is following up on preventive measures adopted by the government and, although he cannot prohibit it, he recommends that tourist visits be avoided. As Favela Tour, Favela Experience and Favela Walking Tour agencies said they were no longer visiting.\nAnother address that arouses the interest of tourists is the [[Santa Marta]] community, also in the [[south]] of the city. After a joint decision between the guides and the local commerce, a [[favela]] also stops receiving tourists in the period of 15 days, initiated. \u201cActually, the option was to cancel all meetings. We have received information that the favela is prone to contamination. We don't know how to make money, but health always comes first. The community here helps one another, so the hunger for people will not die. \"\n\nCollectives of [[Santa Marta]] Guides:\n\u2022 Allan Bas\u00edlio (local guide)\n\u2022 Andr\u00e9ia and Paulo ([[Santa Marta]] souvenirs\n\u2022 Barbosa MB (Rio Favela)\n\u2022 Elias Duarte (TouRio - Favela [[Santa Marta]])\n\u2022 Gilson (Favela Scene)\n\u2022 Jean Ren\u00e9 Mandundu - M- Washiwa. (JR Tour).\n\u2022 Jonatas Nogueira (local guide)\n\u2022 Marco Antonio and Mario (Favela Top Tour)\n\u2022 Jose Carlos, Salete Martins and Veronica Moura (Santa Tours)\n\u2022 Sheila Souza and Roberta Souza (Brazilidade)\n\u2022 Thiago Firmino (Favela Santa Marta Tour)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vozdascomunidades.com.br/coronavirus/covid19nasfavelas-turismo-e-cancelado-em-comunidades-da-zona-sul/|title=#COVID19NasFavelas: Turismo \u00e9 cancelado em comunidades da Zona Sul|first=Melissa|last=Cannabrava}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, Residents of [[Favelas]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] suffer from a lack of water amid the coronavirus pandemic. [[Cariocas]] and fluminenses are much more exposed to the proliferation of coronavirus without having water for cleaning, says a specialist. In parts of the [[Baixada Fluminense]] and the [[North]] Zone of [[Rio de Janeiro]] the water does not reach. Among the affected areas are: Chatuba de [[Mesquita, Rio de Janeiro|Mesquita]], Camarista, [[M\u00e9ier]] and [[Complexo do Alem\u00e3o]] communities. The infectious disease doctor and pediatrician Cristiana Meirelles says that without clean running water, the situation of fighting the epidemic becomes catastrophic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/17/moradores-de-comunidades-do-rj-sofrem-com-falta-de-agua-em-meio-a-pandemia-de-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Moradores de comunidades do RJ sofrem com falta de \u00e1gua em meio \u00e0 pandemia de coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319211134/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/17/moradores-de-comunidades-do-rj-sofrem-com-falta-de-agua-em-meio-a-pandemia-de-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \nCufa calls for measures to contain coronavirus in favelas. Government actions do not include the economically fragile, a contingent that totals more than 70 million people, says the organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/cufa-pede-medidas-para-conter-o-coronavirus-nas-favelas/|title=Cufa pede medidas para conter o coronav\u00edrus nas favelas|website=EXAME|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321203956/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/cufa-pede-medidas-para-conter-o-coronavirus-nas-favelas/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Residents' Associations of Complexo do Alem\u00e3o and CRAS (Reference Center for Social Assistance) remain open to respond to urgent requests. The request for everyone to remain in their homes remains valid indefinitely.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vozdascomunidades.com.br/coronavirus/covid19nasfavelas-para-casos-de-urgencia-associacoes-de-moradores-e-cras-permanecem-abertos/|title=#COVID19NasFavelas: Para casos de urg\u00eancia, Associa\u00e7\u00f5es de Moradores e CRAS permanecem abertos|first=Melissa|last=Cannabrava}}</ref>\nFaced with the coronavirus pandemic in [[Brazil]], and the emergency measures taken by the city hall of [[Rio de Janeiro]] and the state government, presidents of residents' associations in [[Complexo do Alem\u00e3o]] call attention to specific actions to prevent contagion and transmission in Rio's favelas. In addition to the lack of water in some locations, not only in [[Complexo do Alem\u00e3o|Alem\u00e3o]] but also in [[Rocinha]], in [[Acari]], in [[Cidade de Deus, Rio de Janeiro|Cidade de Deus]], most residents are unable to afford the costs of buying [[alcohol]] gel.\nThe free distribution of a prevention kit is the solution suggested to Mayor [[Marcelo Crivella]] and [[Governor]] [[Wilson Witzel]]. The kit must have [[alcohol]] gel, gloves and [[mask]] for external use, in addition to [[soap]], [[detergent]], liquid [[alcohol]] for use at home and working environments in the [[favelas]].\n\n\u201cWe need an urgent hygiene kit. We have to hug each other. We are another favelados forgotten by the government, where we are only remembered during election times. A prevention kit is very important and so far nothing! We will obey and be quarantined, but the city and the government had to remain present. \u201d BURUCA, president of the Reservoir association.\n\u201cIt is their obligation to send this kit to us and so far they have done nothing and said nothing. You can't expect the worst to happen. \u201d MARQUINHOS, president of the Nova Bras\u00edlia association.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vozdascomunidades.com.br/coronavirus/covid19nasfavelas-associacoes-de-moradores-do-alemao-pedem-kit-prevencao/|title=#COVID19NasFavelas: Associa\u00e7\u00f5es de moradores do Alem\u00e3o pedem kit preven\u00e7\u00e3o|first=Melissa|last=Cannabrava}}</ref>\n\nThe advancement of coronavirus in Brazil and in the world has been changing everyone's routine, and in order to keep the population attentive to care, in Rio de Janeiro, police and firefighters are already alerting people in areas of agglomerations such as beaches, commercial points and bar environments. In addition, communities will soon have these warnings through the Civil Defense sirens that are spread out to warn of the risk of heavy rain. According to information that the Voice of the Communities found, the warnings are already recorded and will soon be in the daily lives of the communities so that everyone is alert to the necessary preventions against the contagion of the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vozdascomunidades.com.br/coronavirus/prefeitura-vai-usar-sirenes-da-defesa-civil-para-alertar-moradores-das-favelas-sobre-coronavirus/|title=Exclusivo: Governo vai usar sirenes da Defesa Civil para alertar moradores das favelas sobre coronav\u00edrus|first=Claudia|last=Magalh\u00e3es}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, With the arrival of the pandemic of the new coronavirus (Covid-19) in Brazil, much has been said about the care that the person has to adopt to avoid spreading the disease. However, many of these recommendations like \"stay at home\" are not an option for many Brazilians.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jornalspnorte.com.br/o-coronavirus-no-olhar-das-periferias/|title=O coronav\u00edrus no olhar das periferias|first=Lucas|last=Antonio|date=20 March 2020|website=Jornal SP Norte|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321201643/https://www.jornalspnorte.com.br/o-coronavirus-no-olhar-das-periferias/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Without piped water and space for isolation, Rio's favelas lack the resources to fight the coronavirus. Government authorities are not doing the proper planning that these communities need. \"We are talking about places where there is no running water, there is a lot of mud, a lot of animals. People are unable to maintain the personal hygiene and cleanliness required at this time, \"says one resident.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publico.pt/2020/03/21/mundo/noticia/coronavirus-favelas-rio-janeiro-recursos-basicos-enfrentar-pandemia-1908837|title=Sem \u00e1gua canalizada e espa\u00e7o para isolamento, favelas do Rio n\u00e3o t\u00eam recursos para enfrentar o coronav\u00edrus|website=P\u00daBLICO|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321194632/https://www.publico.pt/2020/03/21/mundo/noticia/coronavirus-favelas-rio-janeiro-recursos-basicos-enfrentar-pandemia-1908837|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, Favelas do Rio have 61 suspected cases of the new coronavirus, according to the Department of Health. Of the total, 19 are in [[Cidade de Deus, Rio de Janeiro|Cidade de Deus]], in the West Zone, where the first case was confirmed over the weekend. City Hall installed community taps in eight slums in this Monday (23). The number of confirmed cases are: in Cidade de Deus 19, in [[Rio das Pedras, Rio de Janeiro|Rio das Pedras]] 10, [[Manguinhos, Rio de Janeiro|Manguinhos]] 8, in [[Jacarezinho, Rio de Janeiro|Jacarezinho]] 7 cases, Complexo Lins 4, Jacar\u00e9 2, in Parada de Lucas 2. Already in Acari, Complexo Caju, Complexo da Mar\u00e9 , Pedreira Complex, S\u00e3o Carlos Complex, Mangueira, Rocinha, Vidigal and Vilar Carioca 1 (each). \"The biggest concern is that the favelas will suffer the most. Crowds of people, there are houses here with 5, 6 children in one room. It is worrying, very worrying. If it spreads out here, it will be very sad\", says the leader Thiago Firmino. Rio's favelas suffer from a lack of water and the population is more vulnerable to coronavirus. Public Defender asks for help from residents to organize data and take emergency measures. Trajano reported that some areas of Mar\u00e9 have been without water for two days while others have not received water for two weeks. \"If the water arrives, it is always with the help of a pump bought by the resident. We have already complained to Cedae, the company said it is resolving, but we already know that the favela is always the last to receive everything and that the rights only come after a lot of collection \".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://s2.glbimg.com/_pbfQW3RR8K11JBZvO2u590X8FM=/0x41:720x861/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/v/O/AA9BvNRQSiodWbwzkd2w/jacarezinho.jfif |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324094915/https://s2.glbimg.com/_pbfQW3RR8K11JBZvO2u590X8FM%3D/0x41:720x861/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/v/O/AA9BvNRQSiodWbwzkd2w/jacarezinho.jfif |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-tem-63-casos-suspeitos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324154450/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-tem-63-casos-suspeitos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brasildefato.com.br/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-sofrem-com-falta-d-agua-e-populacao-fica-mais-vulneravel-a-coronavirus |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324094920/https://www.brasildefato.com.br/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-sofrem-com-falta-d-agua-e-populacao-fica-mais-vulneravel-a-coronavirus |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Healthcare===\n\n[[File:Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade - Boletim Epidemiologico Novo Coronav\u00edrus 2019-nCoV.pdf|thumb|Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade - Boletim Epidemiologico Novo Coronav\u00edrus 2019-nCoV]]\n\nOn 23 January, faced with cases of respiratory disease in [[China]], caused by the new coronavirus, the [[Ministry of Health]] installed, this Wednesday (01/22), the Emergency Operations Center ([[COE]]) - new coronavirus. The committee's objective is to prepare the public health system to deal with possible cases in Brazil. So far, there is no detection of any suspected cases in the country. The portfolio has been carrying out daily monitoring of the situation with the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO), which has been monitoring the issue since the first reports of cases in [[Wuhan]], [[China]], on December 31, 2019. The [[Ministry of Health]] conducted this Thursday (23), in [[Bras\u00edlia]], a technical press conference to clarify doubts about the virus and inform the actions that the portfolio has taken, with the state and municipal health departments, in addition to other bodies, for a possible treatment of a suspected case in the country. During the press conference, the acting Health Minister, [[Jo\u00e3o Gabbardo]], highlighted that the portfolio will continue to inform Brazilian society as the situation updates by the WHO. \u201cThe Ministry of Health has an obligation to clarify and not generate unnecessary panic in the population and we are working together with the state departments for this purpose. Our laboratory network is prepared to carry out the tests and make the diagnostics \", highlighted Jo\u00e3o Gabbardo.\n\nThe COE is composed of technicians specialized in responding to public health emergencies. In addition to the [[Ministry of Health]], the group includes the Pan American Health Organization ([[PAHO]] / [[WHO]]), the National Health Surveillance Agency ([[Anvisa]]), the Evandro Chagas Institute ([[IEC]]), and other bodies. In this way, the country will be able to respond in a unified and immediate way to the entry of the virus in [[Brazilian]] territory. The [[Ministry of Health]] provides basic care to reduce the overall risk of acute [[respiratory]] [[infections]]. Among the guidelines are: avoid close contact with people suffering from acute respiratory infections; perform frequent hand washing, especially after direct contact with sick people or the environment; avoid close contact with wild [[animals]] and [[sick]] animals on [[farms]] or farms.\n\nSince learning about the cases of severe [[pneumonia]] in [[China]], the [[Brazilian Federal Government]] has adopted several actions to monitor and improve the country's capacity to act. These actions include the adoption of measures recommended by WHO; the notification of the [[Ports]], [[Airports]] and [[Borders]] area of \u200b\u200bthe National Health Surveillance Agency ([[Anvisa]]); the notification of the [[Animal Surveillance]] area of \u200b\u200bthe [[Ministry of Agriculture]], Livestock and Supply ([[MAPA]]); and the notification to the Health Departments of the States and Municipalities, other [[Secretariats]] of [[the Ministry of Health]] and other [[federal]] agencies based on official data, avoiding restrictive and disproportionate measures in relation to the risks to the health and transit of people, goods and goods.<ref>{{cite web | last=Sa\u00fade | first=Minist\u00e9rio da | title=Brasil prepara rede de sa\u00fade para novo coronav\u00edrus | website=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade | date=2020-01-23 | url=https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46219-brasil-prepara-rede-de-saude-para-novo-coronavirus | language=pt | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nSince the first cases were reported in the country, there were concerns if its [[Sistema \u00danico de Sa\u00fade|healthcare system]] would be able to deal with the pandemic.\n\nOn 18 March, hospitals in [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]] denounced a lack of health materials, such as masks, gloves and [[hand sanitizer]], caused by an in an increase in prices.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/03/19/funcionarios-relatam-falta-de-alcool-gel-e-luvas-em-hospitais-de-sao-paulo.htm|title=Funcion\u00e1rios relatam falta de \u00e1lcool gel e luvas em hospitais de S\u00e3o Paulo|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175759/https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/03/19/funcionarios-relatam-falta-de-alcool-gel-e-luvas-em-hospitais-de-sao-paulo.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web|url=https://brasil.elpais.com/sociedade/2020-03-20/profissionais-relatam-precariedade-contra-coronavirus-no-sus-paciente-fica-exposto-e-nos-tambem.html|title=Profissionais relatam precariedade contra coronav\u00edrus no SUS: \"Paciente fica exposto, e n\u00f3s tamb\u00e9m\"|first=Joana|last=Oliveira|date=20 March 2020|website=EL PA\u00cdS|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182411/https://brasil.elpais.com/sociedade/2020-03-20/profissionais-relatam-precariedade-contra-coronavirus-no-sus-paciente-fica-exposto-e-nos-tambem.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> According to them, packages of masks went from R$4.50 in January to R$140 on 17 March. The government said it will negotiate with the industry to meet the demand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/coronavirus-hospitais-de-sp-denunciam-falta-de-materiais-e-aumento-de-ate-30-vezes-nos-precos.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Hospitais de SP denunciam falta de materiais e aumento de at\u00e9 30 vezes nos pre\u00e7os|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175759/https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/coronavirus-hospitais-de-sp-denunciam-falta-de-materiais-e-aumento-de-ate-30-vezes-nos-precos.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/brasil/coronavirus-caixa-de-mascara-sobe-de-r-450-para-r-140-denunciam-hospitais/|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Caixa de m\u00e1scara sobe de R$ 4,50 para R$ 140, denunciam Hospitais|first=Reda\u00e7\u00e3o Jornal de|last=Bras\u00edlia|date=18 March 2020|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175758/https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/brasil/coronavirus-caixa-de-mascara-sobe-de-r-450-para-r-140-denunciam-hospitais/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], there was an outage of masks and hand sanitizer in the local commerce.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bahianoticias.com.br/noticia/245528-mascaras-para-profissionais-de-saude-esgotam-em-salvador-e-ambulantes-aproveitam.html|title=M\u00e1scaras para profissionais de sa\u00fade esgotam em Salvador e ambulantes 'aproveitam'|website=bahianoticias.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182417/https://www.bahianoticias.com.br/noticia/245528-mascaras-para-profissionais-de-saude-esgotam-em-salvador-e-ambulantes-aproveitam.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nRio and five other municipalities in the state declare an emergency to contain the coronavirus. Municipalities of [[S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo, Rio de Janeiro|S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo]] and [[Guapimirim]] also declared a state of emergency and [[Niter\u00f3i]], [[Nova Igua\u00e7u]] and Mesquita declared an emergency situation in the area of public health.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nOn 19 March, scientists predicted up to 2&nbsp;million deaths in Brazil in the worst scenario without measures to contain the coronavirus. They point out that maintaining social distance is one of the most effective measures without a vaccine.<ref name=\"auto10\"/> Their conclusion came after analyzing the [[Growth curve (statistics)|growth curve]] of COVID-19 cases in Brazil. The contagion rate is the same as that registered in Italy, as the number of infected people has been doubling every 54 hours. According to estimates, the number of confirmed cases might reach 3,000 by 24 March.<ref name=\"auto13\"/> According to the Ministry of Health, the number of infected patients will grow [[Exponential growth|exponentially]] by the end of June.<ref name=\"exame\"/>\nThe mayor of [[Belo Horizonte]], [[Alexandre Kalil]] (PSD), asked General Altair Jos\u00e9 Polsin, commander of the 4th Army Region, for the temporary assignment of 51 professionals from the army garrison to assist in the demands of fighting the coronavirus. The Brazilian Army has not yet said whether it will meet this demand. Peak cases of Covid-19 in BH will be in the 1st week of April. In an interview, the health secretary announced the creation of two more Respiratory Disease centers and is studying placing PMs to serve the population.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/minas-gerais/pico-de-casos-de-covid-19-em-bh-sera-na-1-semana-de-abril-19032020|title=Pico de casos de Covid-19 em BH ser\u00e1 na 1\u00aa semana de abril|date=19 March 2020|website=R7.com|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322190809/https://noticias.r7.com/minas-gerais/pico-de-casos-de-covid-19-em-bh-sera-na-1-semana-de-abril-19032020|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/19/coronavirus-prefeitura-de-bh-pede-reforco-de-medicos-ao-exercito.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Prefeitura de BH pede refor\u00e7o do Ex\u00e9rcito para o atendimento da sa\u00fade|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173852/https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/19/coronavirus-prefeitura-de-bh-pede-reforco-de-medicos-ao-exercito.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto5\"/> \nGovernment of RS decrees public calamity situation due to coronaviruses. Among the measures are the prohibition of interstate travel and the restriction of items purchased in the markets. Decree applies from this Thursday (19).<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\nEmployees at four public hospitals in the city of S\u00e3o Paulo reported a shortage of materials such as alcohol gel, masks and gloves when caring for patients with suspected coronavirus (covid-19). Professionals report precariousness against coronavirus in the SUS: \u201cThe patient is exposed, and so are we\u201d. With a shortage of masks and even rationing of gel alcohol, the situation of public service workers is different from that of private reference hospitals in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref name=\"auto8\"/><ref name=\"auto7\"/>\nStores specializing in medical supplies no longer have alcohol gels and masks. Among them, those known as N95, used by health professionals. With the worldwide coronavirus pandemic and the great search for protection, street vendors (without sales in the middle of the pandemic crisis) have been taking advantage of the demand for equipment and trying to profit from it.<ref name=\"auto4\"/>\n\n[[File:Capacita\u00e7\u00e3o dos profissionais da Sa\u00fade que atuar\u00e3o nos terminais de \u00f4nibus - 49667698972.jpg|thumb|Health professionals clean up public transport to prevent spread]]\n\nOn 20 March, it was reported by the press that Brazil was contradicting the recommendation of the [[World Health Organization]] by only testing patients in severe condition. Jo\u00e3o Gabbardo, executive secretary at the Ministry of Health, said that the criteria adopted would not change, and people with serious cases will be tested for COVID-19.<ref name=\"auto2\"/> The following day, a group of scientists announced they were developing new COVID-19 tests in Brazil. They expect to elaborate a test which will work with a single drop of blood from the patient. They expect it to be ready for the current outbreak of COVID-19, and hope to engage some of the main Brazilian universities in its development.<ref name=\"auto6\"/>\nWithout protective items, health workers improvise caps like masks in hospitals. In addition to the first cases of coronavirus in Acre, health professionals in the state have to deal with the lack of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE). Some agents are improvising caps like masks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://istoe.com.br/sem-itens-de-protecao-agentes-de-saude-improvisam-toucas-como-mascaras-em-hospitais/|title=Sem itens de prote\u00e7\u00e3o, agentes de sa\u00fade improvisam toucas como m\u00e1scaras em hospitais|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\nHealth professionals in RJ complain about the lack of conditions to work with patients in Covid-19. Doctor says there are no N95 masks, with more efficient filter, at Hospital Salgado Filho. Unions say there is a shortage of personal protective equipment in hospitals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/20/profissionais-de-saude-do-rj-reclamam-da-falta-de-condicoes-para-trabalhar-com-pacientes-de-covid-19.ghtml|title=Profissionais de sa\u00fade do RJ reclamam da falta de condi\u00e7\u00f5es para trabalhar com pacientes de Covid-19|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182757/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/20/profissionais-de-saude-do-rj-reclamam-da-falta-de-condicoes-para-trabalhar-com-pacientes-de-covid-19.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Religious services===\n[[Odilo Scherer|Dom Odilo Scherer]], [[archdiocese of S\u00e3o Paulo|Archbishop of S\u00e3o Paulo]] had initially defended that churches should not be closed, arguing that there should be more daily services to diffuse large gatherings. Later, he determined the suspension of celebrations with the people. <ref name=igrejas/><ref>{{cite web|title=Comunicado sobre a suspens\u00e3o tempor\u00e1ria de Celebra\u00e7\u00f5es Religiosas|url=http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-sobre-a-suspensao-temporaria-de-celebracoes-religiosas|date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326200303/http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-sobre-a-suspensao-temporaria-de-celebracoes-religiosas|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Comunicado n\u00b02 da Arquidiocese de S\u00e3o Paulo sobre Celebra\u00e7\u00f5es e outras A\u00e7\u00f5es Pastorais nas igrejas durante a pandemia do Coronav\u00edrus|url=http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-ndeg2-da-arquidiocese-de-sao-paulo-sobre-celebracoes-e-outras-acoes-pastorais-nas-igrejas-durante-a-pandemia-do-coronavirus|date=26 March 2020|access-date=28 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331203026/http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-ndeg2-da-arquidiocese-de-sao-paulo-sobre-celebracoes-e-outras-acoes-pastorais-nas-igrejas-durante-a-pandemia-do-coronavirus|archive-date=31 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Bishop [[Edir Macedo]], founder of the [[Universal Church of the Kingdom of God]] has also defended that services should not be suspended, as well as [[Silas Malafaia]], leader of [[Assembleias de Deus|Assembleia de Deus Vit\u00f3ria em Cristo]].<ref name=igrejas>{{cite web|url=https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-20/igrejas-desafiam-recomendacao-de-suspender-missas-e-cultos-diante-da-pandemia-do-coronavirus.html|title=Igrejas desafiam recomenda\u00e7\u00e3o de suspender missas e cultos diante da pandemia do coronav\u00edrus|first=Breiller|last=Pires|date=20 March 2020|website=EL PA\u00cdS|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321155318/https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-20/igrejas-desafiam-recomendacao-de-suspender-missas-e-cultos-diante-da-pandemia-do-coronavirus.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Malafaia said he would only close his churches if mandated by a court order. Macedo has caused greater controversy after he dismissed coronavirus as a creation of the media.\n<ref>{{cite web|title=M\u00f4nica Bergamo: V\u00eddeo mostra Edir Macedo dizendo que coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 inofensivo e que Satan\u00e1s e m\u00eddia promovem medo|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/video-mostra-edir-macedo-dizendo-que-coronavirus-e-inofensivo-e-que-satanas-e-midia-promovem-medo.shtml|date=15 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064430/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/video-mostra-edir-macedo-dizendo-que-coronavirus-e-inofensivo-e-que-satanas-e-midia-promovem-medo.shtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Television programming===\nBrazilian networks started airing prevention tips during their programming. [[Rede Globo|Globo]], [[Sistema Brasileiro de Televis\u00e3o|SBT]], [[RecordTV]] e [[RedeTV!]] announced they would suspend the production of ''[[telenovelas]]'', and would record their [[talk shows]] without a live audience, while expanding journalism in their programming.<ref>{{cite web | last=Padiglione | first=Cristina | title=Em razao do coronavirus, Domingao do Faustao vai ao ar sem plateia pela 1 vez em 31 anos | publisher=[[Folha de S.Paulo]] | date=12 March 2020 | url=https://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/em-razao-coronavirus-domingao-faustao-vai-ao-ar-sem-plateia-pela-1a-vez-em-31-anos | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064434/https://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/em-razao-coronavirus-domingao-faustao-vai-ao-ar-sem-plateia-pela-1a-vez-em-31-anos | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Oliveira | first=Fernando | title=Com medo do coronavirus, Raul Gil cancela grava\u00c7ao e se isola em sitio | publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL]] | date=13 March 2020 | url=https://tvefamosos.uol.com.br/colunas/fefito/2020/03/13/com-medo-do-coronavirus-raul-gil-se-isola-em-sitio.html | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064431/https://tvefamosos.uol.com.br/colunas/fefito/2020/03/13/com-medo-do-coronavirus-raul-gil-se-isola-em-sitio.html | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=RedeTV! cancela plateia do Encrenca com medo do surto de coronavirus | publisher=[[Universo Online|Noticias da TV \u2013 UOL]] | date=12 March 2020 | url=https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/televisao/redetv-cancela-plateia-do-encrenca-com-medo-do-surto-de-coronavirus-34432 | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064431/https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/televisao/redetv-cancela-plateia-do-encrenca-com-medo-do-surto-de-coronavirus-34432 | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\nThese are the graphs related to the numbers of cases and deaths in each state of the country.\n\n===New cases per day===\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=700\n|colors=#2980B9,#A500