Heights: Dalat and the Making and Undoing of French Indochina'' (2010).\n* Lawrence, Adria. ''Imperial rule and the politics of nationalism: anti-colonial protest in the French empire'' (Cambridge UP, 2013).\n* {{cite journal |first=C. W. |last=Newbury |first2=A. S. |last2=Kanya-Forstner |title=French Policy and the Origins of the Scramble for West Africa |journal=The Journal of African History |volume=10 |issue=2 |year=1969 |pages=253\u2013276 |jstor=179514 |doi=10.1017/S0021853700009518 }}.\n* Klein, Martin A. ''Slavery and colonial rule in French West Africa'' (Cambridge University Press, 1998)\n* Manning, Patrick. ''Francophone Sub-Saharan Africa 1880-1995'' (Cambridge UP, 1998). [https://www.questia.com/library/105166398/francophone-sub-saharan-africa-1880-1995 online]\n* Neres, Philip. ''French-speaking West Africa: From Colonial Status to Independence'' (1962) [https://www.questia.com/library/7131716/french-speaking-west-africa-from-colonial-status online]\n* Priestley, Herbert Ingram. ''France overseas: a study of modern imperialism'' (1938) 464pp.\n* Quinn, Frederick. ''The French Overseas Empire'' (2000) [https://www.questia.com/library/1896884/the-french-overseas-empire online]\n* {{cite book |first=Thomas |last=Pakenham |title=The Scramble for Africa, 1876\u20131912 |url=https://archive.org/details/scrambleforafric00pake |url-access=registration |year=1991 |location=New York |publisher=Random House |isbn=978-0-394-51576-2}}.\n* {{cite book |first=Maria |last=Petringa |title=Brazza, A Life for Africa |year=2006 |location=Bloomington, IN |publisher=AuthorHouse |isbn=978-1-4259-1198-0}}.\n* Priestley, Herbert Ingram. (1938) ''France overseas;: A study of modern imperialism'' 463pp; encyclopedic coverage as of late 1930s\n* Roberts, Stephen H. ''History of French Colonial Policy (1870-1925)'' (2 vol 1929) [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.84402 vol 1 online] also [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.89866 vol 2 online]; Comprehensive s