avbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2019-20 Mercyhurst Lakers women's ice hockey season}}\n[[Category:2019\u201320 NCAA Division I women's hockey season|Mercyhurst]]\n[[Category:Mercyhurst Lakers women's ice hockey seasons]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in Pennsylvania|Mercy]]\n[[Category:2020 in sports in Pennsylvania|Mercy]]\n", "text_old": "{{NCAAIceHockeyTeamSeason\n  |Image =\n  |ImageSize = 200px\n  |Season = [[2019-20 NCAA Division I women's ice hockey season|2019\u201320]]\n  |Team = Mercyhurst Lakers\n  |Sex = women\n  |Conference = College Hockey America\n  |ShortConference = College Hockey America\n  |ConferenceRank = 1st\n  |Poll#1 = USA Today/USA Hockey Magazine\n  |Poll#1Rank =    \n  |Poll#2 = USCHO.com\n  |Poll#2Rank =    \n  |Record = 21-10-5\n  |ConfRecord = 13-4-3\n  |HomeRecord = 12-0-4\n  |RoadRecord =  6-9-1\n  |NeutralRecord = 3-1-0 \n  |HeadCoach =   [[Michael Sisti]] <small>(21st season)</small>\n  |AsstCoach1=  Beth Hanrahan   \n  |AsstCoach2=  Kelley Steadman\n  |AsstCoach3=       \n  |Captain = Maggie Knott<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hurstathletics.com/news/2019/5/15/womens-ice-hockey-announces-captains-for-2019-20-season.aspx|date=15 May 2019 | publisher=Mercyhurst University|title=Women's Ice Hockey Announces Captains for 2019-20 Season | accessdate=29 January 2020}}</ref><br>Michele Robillard<br>Alexa Vasko\n  |AltCaptain = \n  |Arena = Mercyhurst Ice Center\n  |Champion = CHA Regular Season Champions, CHA Tournament Champions\n  |NCAATourney = \n  |NCAATourneyResult = \n  |prevseason = [[2018\u201319 Mercyhurst Lakers women's ice hockey season|2018\u201319]]\n  |nextseason = [[2020\u201321 Mercyhurst Lakers women's ice hockey season|2020\u201321]]\n}}\nThe Mercyhurst Lakers represented [[Mercyhurst University]] in [[College Hockey America|CHA women's ice hockey]] during the [[2019-20 NCAA Division I women's ice hockey season]]. The Lakers were undefeated on home ice. Mercyhurst won the College Hockey America Tournament with a 2\u20131 overtime win over regular season champions, Robert Morris. The overtime victory came at 4:19 with a goal from Summer-Rae Dobson. As tournament champions, Mercyhurst earned a berth in the NCAA Tournament to determine the national championship. On March 12, 2020, the NCAA Tournament was cancelled due to the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n==Offseason==\nEmma Nuutinen was part of the Team Finland IIHF World Championship Team that earned Silver Medals  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://hurstathletics.com/news/2019/4/14/womens-ice-hockey-nuutinen-team-finland-earn-first-ever-silver-medal-at-iihf-womens-world-championships.aspx|date=14 April 2019 | publisher=Mercyhurst University|title=Nuutinen, Team Finland Earn First Ever Silver Medal at IIHF Women's World Championships | accessdate=29 January 2020}}</ref>.\n\n===Recruiting===\n\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hurstathletics.com/news/2019/7/2/silvonen-to-join-womens-ice-hockey-for-2019-20-season.aspx|date=2 July 2019 | publisher=Mercyhurst University|title=Silvonen to Join Women's Ice Hockey for 2019-20 Season | accessdate=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"80%\"\n|- align=\"center\"  style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Mercyhurst Lakers|color=white}}\"\n| '''Player''' || '''Position''' ||'''Nationality''' || '''Notes'''\n\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\" \"\n|  Aubrey Cole ||  Defense   || {{CAN}}    || Played with Bluewater Jr. Hawks\n\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#ccffcc\"\n|  Gabrielle Cox||  Forward   || {{USA}}    || Defender for the Boston Jr. Eagles\n\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\" \"\n|  Jordan Mortlock||  Defense   || {{CAN}}    || Selected for Team Alberta\n\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#ccffcc\"\n|  Abigail Schauer ||  Forward   || {{USA}}    || Attended USA National Team Camp twice\n\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\" \"\n|  Jenna Silvonen || Goaltender    || {{FIN}}    || On Silver Medal Finland Team with Emma Nuutinen\n\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#ccffcc\"\n|  Alexandria Weiss || Defense   || {{USA}}    || Played f